title: frozen pies
directions: Brown the coconut and pecans in 1/4 stick oleo, stir often, then cool.
Mix the cream cheese and milk, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 mixture in each pie crust.
Put 1/4 caramel over this mixture, then 1/4 the coconut and pecans.
Repeat and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Boil and mash potatoes; add ingredients (might be less milk). Place potatoes in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Place casserole in fridge.
The day they are to be used, bring to room temperature and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until they bubble.
Serves 8.

title: martha pippens' tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick and clear, then add jello.
Pour this mixture over berries which are already in pie shell.
Chill well, then top with whipped cream.

title: quick oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand for 15 minutes. Blend butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs, flour, cinnamon, vanilla, soda and raisins.
Bake in 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Put in baking dish; put in chicken pieces on top. Cover with stuffing.
Mix oleo and stuffing; sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, folding in Cool Whip and refrigerate for 1 hour and serve.

title: potato donuts
directions: Beat potatoes, sugar and melted butter together.
Add the beaten eggs, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and milk; beat.
Stir in about 5 cups flour.
Pat out on floured surface; drop into hot oil.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large saucepan.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Will keep a very long time.

title: holiday soda bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash the raisins leaving them slightly moist.

title: baked cheese spread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with unsalted crackers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and mix together.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream all ingredients, except shrimp and cocktail sauce, together.
Add the shrimp, after it has been washed and drained on paper towels.
Place on a nonmetallic dish.
When ready to serve, add cocktail seafood sauce; spread on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef, drain, add onions and green peppers. Saute until soft, add rest of ingredients and bring to boil. Reduce
heat and simmer covered 15-30 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: salsa cruda
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Place in bowl.
Add onion, jalapenos, cilantro, oil, garlic and salt.
Serve with nacho chips or as a topping on Mexican foods.

title: kentucky spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together 3 1/2 cups sugar, shortening, spices, salt and baking soda.
Add the molasses and blend well.
Gradually mix in the flour.
Then add the water to make a dough of pie crust consistency.
For each cookie, take 1 teaspoon of dough and roll it into a ball, then roll the ball in sugar.
Place each on ungreased cookie sheet, make a small indentation in the top of each ball and fill with a dot of jelly. Bake for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with sugar.
Cool before storing.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and orange flavoring.
Add orange slices, sliced and drained.
Mix.
Bake in two or three greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool. Mix pineapple (with its juice) and pudding mix.
Let set for five minutes.
Fold in vanilla and Cool Whip.
Fill between layers and frost.
Refrigerate.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. In large bowl, combine oat bran cereal, nuts, raisins and baking powder. Stir in honey. Mix milk, eggs whites and oil together (in small bowl). Blend in with oat bran mixture. Line muffin pans with paper baking cups and fill with batter. Bake 15-17 min. Make 12 muffins.

title: crab salad(one serving)
directions: In medium bowl, stir together ranch dressing, mayonnaise, horseradish, lemon juice, pepper and cumin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour until chilled.

title: hot spinach or broccoli dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break bread in pieces and bake about 15 minutes.
Saute celery, pepper and onion in margarine.
Add cheese. Stir over low heat until melted.
Stir in remainder of ingredients. Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Serve hot with bread pieces and/or vegetable dippers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn casserole(a trace of fat)
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart glass dish in microwave.
In large bowl mix remaining ingredients (except onions).
Stir until mixed well; bake one hour at 350°, uncovered.
Add diced onions on top (optional).

title: chinese walnut chicken
directions: In skillet, toast walnuts in hot oil, stirring constantly. Remove nuts to paper towel.
Put chicken into skillet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cook, stirring frequently, 5 to 10 minutes or until slightly tender.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce and cooking sherry;
add remaining chicken broth.
Pour over vegetables in skillet.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Add chicken, bamboo shoots, water chestnuts and walnuts.
Heat through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas meat balls
directions: Mix chili sauce, cranberry sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Simmer until cranberry sauce is dissolved.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, mustard and seasoned salt.
Add potatoes and then rest of the ingredients.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add butter, lemon rind, juice and egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Cool 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix seasoning with margarine.
Put 1/2 crumbs in casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients; add to casserole.
Put remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grammy's kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
On a cookie sheet, lay out a single row of pretzels.
Unwrap chocolate kiss from its foil and place one on top of each pretzel.
Place cookie sheet in oven for about 3 to 5 minutes until chocolate kiss is just soft.
Remove cookie sheet from oven.
Place an M&M on top of each kiss and lightly press M&M down into chocolate kiss to secure.
Let cool completely before storing.

title: macaroni-ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on macaroni package; drain.
Combine macaroni with ham, undiluted soup, water and onion.
Arrange in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover for last 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar doughnuts
directions: Melt Crisco
to
make
1-inch
deep; heat to 365°.
Mix pancake mix and
sugar.
Add
milk
and
egg;
stir just until pancake mix is
moistened.
At once, drop a few at a time into Crisco.
Brown doughnuts on both sides.
Drain on paper towel. Shake in bag with cinnamon and sugar (or) confectioners sugar. Makes 3 dozen (1 3/4-inch) doughnut balls.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Add eggs, milk and oil (or applesauce) to cake mix.
Mix with fork. Add frosting, 1/3 at a time, with electric mixer on low speed.
Grease and flour tube pan. Spread the chopped nuts on bottom of pan; pour batter over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Remove from pan.
Gets better each day!

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and milk.
Then add vanilla and Grape-Nuts.
Mix again in glass baking dish.
Set in pan of water to bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Keep in tightly covered bowl in refrigerator.
Will keep 7 days.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Empty some of cranberry juice into a glass.
Pour sugar into cranberry juice and shake to dissolve.
Pour all ingredients together over ice.

title: creole shrimp dip
directions: In small bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill.

title: company coming casserole
directions: Fry meat and onion together.
Add seasonings to drained meat and onion.
Mix soup, tomatoes and beans together in large pan starting with chips, then meat, cheese.
Repeat first layer.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy crock-pot chicken dinner
directions: Mix cream of chicken and milk. In crock-pot, put in chicken, salt and pepper, then soup. Layer again. Cover and bake 4 hours on high or 6 hours on low. When done, uncover; sprinkle onions on top and put in oven, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes to crunch up onions.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute chopped celery and onion in the butter.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased Pyrex dish and bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Drink 1/4 cup each night before going to bed.
(I drink 1/2 cup.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Break crackers and press down into butter.
Add chicken broth, soup and sour cream. Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 300° until bubbling.

title: lovelight chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Beat
egg whites until frothy, gradually adding 1/2 cup sugar. Beat
until
very	stiff.	Sift
the
remaining sugar, flour, soda
and
salt into another bowl.	Add oil and half of buttermilk,
egg yolks and chocolate.
Beat 150 strokes.
Fold in meringue.
Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together the white and brown sugar and cooking oil. Stir in eggs, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add oats, coconut, cornflakes, chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Fix Jell-O according to package.
Drain the pineapple and add it to the Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese.
Let set.
Top with whipped topping.
You can add nuts to this before it sets, if you want to.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Put tortilla chips in sturdy plastic bag and crumble with rolling pin.
Set aside in bowl.
Melt butter in small bowl in microwave and add taco seasoning; stir.
Coat chicken with butter mixture and dredge in tortilla chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with sour cream or salsa.

title: blueberry treat
directions: Melt butter, add flour and nuts.
Press into bottom of pan and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Mix whipped topping, cream cheese, and sugar.
Beat until thick.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with blueberries.

title: dinosaur food
directions: Mix dirt and swamp water in a pan.
Add bones and fat.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Add grass and squashed bugs.
Boil mixture 1 minute.
Cool dinosaur food and place it on wax paper by spoonfuls.
Now call your dinosaurs to eat!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls out onto an 11 x 17-inch sheet pan.
Mash perforations together.
Bake according to the directions on the can.
Mix dressing, Miracle Whip, cream cheese and sour cream. Smooth on cooled crust.
Spread or sprinkle vegetables on top of cheese mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap or wax paper and press vegetables into cheese mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Keep, covered and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Combine first six ingredients; sprinkle lemon juice over apples, then add dry mixture; stir well.
Let sit for 5 minutes before putting in crust.
Cover with top crust, make slits to vent steam and brush lightly with milk.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then turn oven to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes more, or until crust is browned and filling is bubbly.

title: stew beef casserole
directions: Place beef in covered Pyrex casserole dish.
Cover with onion soup.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Cook at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.
This can be frozen.

title: gobs
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Alternate liquid and flour. Drop teaspoonfuls on ungreased pan and bake 7 minutes at 450°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Stir up flour and sugar.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Add to flour and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
Stir good. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a small nonmetal bowl, cook in microwave butter, uncovered, on 100% power for 30 seconds to 1 minutes or till melted. Stir in beaten eggs, corn syrup, sugar, and flour. Micro-cook, uncovered, on 50% of power about 5 minutes or till slightly thickened, stirring every minutes. Stir in vanilla. Turn into pecan pie pastry. Arrange pecan halves atop of pie. Micro-cook, uncovered, on 30% power for 6 to 7 minutes or just till set, rotating the dish a quarter-turn
every 2 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: white wine pound cake
directions: Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Heat only while sugar is no longer grainy.
Pour over warm cake.
Allow to stand 30 minutes before turning out.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in a jar.
Heat 1 cup water; add 2 teaspoons tea.

title: sour cream shrimp dip
directions: Melt butter in medium size heavy saucepan; saute onion and celery until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir into vegetable mixture; blend.
Stir in shrimp, pepper and hot sauce.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until warm throughout.
Do not boil!
Transfer to serving container.
Garnish with green onion and shrimp.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: fudge(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 6 minutes.
Remove from fire and add remainder of ingredients.
Beat until mixture thickens and then quickly remove to buttered pan.
Cut in squares when cool but not entirely cold.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix sugar, water and citric acid; cook together until dissolved.
Cool.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice to make syrup.
Mix 1 part syrup and 3 parts water.
Use food coloring for desired color.

title: mountain blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix blackberries with sugar.
Cook approximately 15 minutes. Mix cornstarch with water; pour in with berries and stir.
Pour into 7 x 10-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick, eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Drizzle over hot berries.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spam dinner
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in baking dish.
Make partial cuts in Spam and place in dish.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix eggs, salt, and vanilla together.
Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan, add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add this to egg mixture and beat well.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: basic waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron until it is smoking hot.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Combine the yolks, milk and shortening.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients all at once; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in gently into batter. Bake until steaming stops and waffles are golden.

title: island sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix egg, crumbs, onion, milk and salt.
Add meat.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs with shortening in skillet.
Bake at 450° in oven to brown.
On top of stove, in same skillet, drain off fat.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to syrup to make 3/4 cup.

title: lime ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add ice cream and stir until mixed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate in 9 x 9-inch pan. Serves 9.

title: chocolate caramel pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 inch square pan.
In medium bowl, combine powdered sugar, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 tablespoon whipping cream; blend well. Add flour, mix until crumbly. With floured hands, press evenly in greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm to the touch.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix pork, beef, salt, pepper, brown sugar and rice together. Wilt cabbage leaves by boiling until they separate easily from the head.
Roll 1 1/2 inch balls of meat and 1 Tbsp. sauerkraut in each cabbage leaf.
If leaves are bigger, they can be cut in half.

title: low-fat jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in buttermilk and pineapple and refrigerate until set.

title: lana's magic caramel icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large (tall) saucepan and mix well.
Cook to soft-ball stage, stirring constantly, and remove from heat.
Beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Great for ribs or chicken.

title: one bowl macaroons
directions: Mix all together; drop by spoonfuls 1-inch apart on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
onion in frying pan; sprinkle in bottom of
pie pan.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over meat. Pat mashed
potatoes onto the soup and sprinkle cheese on the top. Bake for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and cook in oil until no longer pink.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Pour over cooked macaroni and top with shredded cheese.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Cook, without stirring, to 260° on candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a hard ball).
In mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a thin stream into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull.
(Mixture may become too stiff for mixer.) Fold in nuts. Drop mixture from tip of buttered spoon onto waxed paper.
Yields about 4 dozen candies.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: In a saucepan, heat raisins and water to just boiling.
Cool. Mix egg, sugar and vanilla.
Add to raisins.
Add flour and dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put uncooked rice and water with salt and pepper in casserole dish.
Lay chicken over top of rice.
Cover with soups and bake at 350° until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into rounded ball; roll in crushed nuts.

title: cookie cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Bring to boil oleo, Crisco and water.
Mix eggs, soda, cinnamon and milk.
Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lazy day beef stew
directions: Cut onion into small pieces.
Tenderize beef cubes and cut into small pieces.
Add desired vegetables (we like potatoes, carrots, beans and celery in ours), tomato sauce and water.
Cover large baking dish and bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: cherry jello mold
directions: Stir all ingredients together (except sour cream).
Divide in half.
Refrigerate half and let other half at room temperature. When first half is firm, spread on sour cream, then pour rest of jello on top.
Return to refrigerator.

title: bavarian party dip
directions: Saute onions 8 to 10 minutes.
Take off heat and drain.
Mix meat and cream cheese; add onions and pepper.
Combine well.
Use as spread on crackers or party rye.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following directions for low cholesterol recipe.
Stir cinnamon into frosting.
Frost top and sides of cake.

title: caramel candy bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and milk in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth; remove from heat and reserve.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Stir in egg and margarine with fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press half of the crumbly mixture in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Drizzle with caramel mixture. Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.
Loosen edges from sides of pan.
Cool completely.
Yields 48 bars.

title: breakfast crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla, beat well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in cereals and any ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: green beans mexicali
directions: In a large pot, fry the bacon until done.
Remove all but about 2 tablespoons of the bacon dripping. Add the green beans, onion, salt, pepper, Ro-Tel tomatoes and water to the pot. Simmer on medium for about 45 minutes. Add water as needed.
Carefully stir to coat beans.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a dishpan or very, very large bowl.
Put about 6 on cookie sheet.
Bake at about 275° or until done (12 minutes).
Let rest before removing from cookie sheet. Makes a large batch of cookies.

title: zesty chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 24 hours.
Put onion and garlic croutons and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese into a Ziploc bag and crunch up with rolling pin.
Drain off extra Italian dressing.
Place chicken in bag with croutons and shake.
Make sure chicken is well coated. Place on cookie sheet; bake at 325° until tender (do not overcook) for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until done.
Put everything in the crock-pot on high for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, vanilla and shortening until fluffy.
Add cake mix and stir until mixed well.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful on slightly greased cookie sheet approximately 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes. Cookies will be soft in center when done.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix lightly.
Place mixture in a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine sugar and vinegar in a small saucepan; cook over low heat until sugar melts, stirring constantly.
Pour over ham loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: bertha ramirez tacos
directions: Butter tortillas.
Put cooked meat into tortillas.
Add cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Roll up and serve.

title: vegetable beef casserole
directions: Saute onion and meat in butter.
Add vegetables and soup. Pour in buttered casserole.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pears
directions: In a small bowl, combine apricots and pecans.
Use fork to mash 1 tablespoon margarine into fruit.
Set aside.
Cut pears in half. Dip out core, leaving 1/2-inch hole in each piece.
Place in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Fill each pear with apricot mixture. In measuring cup:
place syrup and remaining 3 tablespoons of margarine, melted.
Microwave until pears are tender.
Baste at least once.
(Or bake in conventional oven.)

title: grated zucchini pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except margarine and cheese.
Melt one tablespoon margarine in nonstick skillet over moderate heat. Add zucchini mixture and cook until golden brown around the edges, 6 to 7 minutes.
Place a large plate over the skillet and invert zucchini mixture onto it.
Add remaining margarine to skillet. Melt.
Slide pancake back into skillet.
Cook, uncovered, until firm.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add rice and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels in a heavy saucepan or in microwave with the cream.
Combine rest of ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts.
Press 3/4 in greased 9 x 19-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Then sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Dribble the caramel mixture and then the remaining crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: jane's praline cookies
directions: Combine egg, margarine, brown sugar and vanilla. Add flour and salt. Stir well. Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Place cranberries, oranges and apples in food processor with metal blade inserted.
Process until finely pureed.
Add sugar; pulse until sugar is thoroughly mixed.
Pour into medium bowl. Cover and refrigerate overnight or longer to enhance flavor. Makes 8 cups.

title: puffy omelet
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Add tomato, green pepper, garlic and onion.
Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Beat in water, salt and pepper.
Fold yolks into the beaten whites.
Melt butter in a 10-inch omelet pan.
Turn mixture into pan and cover.
Cook on low until omelet is puffed and underside is browned.
Place pan, uncovered, in the oven and bake 10 to 15 minutes, until top is dry.
Cut into 4 to 6 wedges; top with reserved tomato mixture and serve at once.

title: domoco delight cake
directions: Cream egg and margarine with sugar until creamy.
Add dry ingredients and remaining ingredients; mix.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in separate bowl.
In an oblong dish, put melted butter and add drained juice from canned fruit (any kind works well or you may use fresh fruit). Pour in pan and stir slightly.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick vegetable spray. Cut bread into 1 1/2-inch slices with serrated knife and arrange closely in a single layer in pan. In bowl, beat eggs lightly. Beat in milk, 1/4 cup of the sugar and vanilla, using whisk. Pour half of egg-milk mixture over bread. Peel, core and slice apples. Arrange apple rings evenly over bread in pan. Pour remaining egg-milk mixture over apples. Mix remaining 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon. Sprinkle evenly over apples. Dot with margarine. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 5 to 10 minutes, then cut into squares and serve with maple syrup.

title: cauliflower-olive salad
directions: Cover cauliflower flowerets, onion and olives with salad dressing.
Marinate overnight.
Just before serving, add lettuce, broken into bite-size pieces.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until cheese melts. Pour into fondue pot and serve warm.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Chill.
Shape in 6 to 8 croquettes, shaping each around a cube of cheese.
Roll in cracker meal. Saute in about 1-inch of hot fat until browned on all sides.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon and mix with cream cheese. Add onion and liquid smoke, mix well. Add enough mayonnaise to make the salmon mixture spread evenly on crackers.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger meat.
Drain meat and add to noodles.
Add soups, sour cream and corn.
Mix in heavy saucepan. Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.
Makes an entire meal.

title: sex on the beach
directions: Mix all ingredients in equal portions in a 1-gallon milk jug. Serve as shot or over ice.

title: pamela's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Serve with tortilla chips. Delicious.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Place in a large bowl with onion and green pepper.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until fairly crisp.
Combine brown sugar (use 1/2 cup for less sweet taste), ketchup and onion soup mix.
Add bacon and drippings.
Stir in beans.
Bake in large casserole at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly around edges.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into thin slices to measure about 4 cups.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce on potatoes.
Cook uncovered in 325° oven 1 hour and 20 minutes or in 375° oven 1 hour.

title: no bake oatmeal drops
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add the oatmeal and nutmeats.
Add the vanilla. Working fast, spoon onto wax paper.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; beat with mixer.
Add flour, spices, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 3 round cake pans.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil the jello, sugar and water.
Remove from heat. Add baby food and pineapple; set aside to cool, being sure that all is dissolved.
Combine softened cream cheese and milk.
Beat again.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: baked luncheon sandwiches
directions: Make
sandwiches
by
placing
cup
ham and 1/2 cup cheese or 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese between 2 slices bread for
each
sandwich.
Arrange close together in buttered baking dish.
Cut	each half diagonally if desired.
Beat egg and milk together;
pour
over
sandwiches.	Let
stand
in refrigerator overnight.	Bake
in
325°	oven for 1 hour until golden brown. Remove
from
oven 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serve with rich cream sauce with mushrooms and a dash of Worcestershire if desired.
Top
with
paprika and a sprig of parsley if desired. Yield: 4 sandwiches or 8 halves.

title: white bread
directions: Mix together:
1 qt. warm water, instant potato, & salt.
Let cool.
Add dry yeast.
Stir in dry milk, sugar, crisco and add flour last.

title: roll-out sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Then roll out and bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a 9 x 13-inch long cake pan layer ingredients in the order given.
Bake for 1 hour or until brown.

title: congo bills
directions: Use regular cake procedures for mixing.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Blend until creamy.
Blend in egg. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded spoonful 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or cook 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Let cool on sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack. Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: cindy's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Measure dry ingredients into a large bowl and stir to mix.
Measure remaining ingredients into a large measuring cup or medium bowl.
Mix together thoroughly and add to dry ingredients.
Stir with wire whisk until dry ingredients are moist.
Pour into a nonstick or lightly oiled 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Put all in crock-pot together and cook until done.

title: macadamia nut and white chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well. Thoroughly combine flour, soda and salt. Stir the flour mixture into the creamed mixture until well blended.

Add a little more flour, if necessary, to make a slightly stiff dough. Stir in chocolate and nuts. Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on non-greased baking sheets. Flatten each cookie slightly. Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Cool cookies a few minutes on baking sheet before transferring to a rack to cool completely.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner according to package directions, adding onion while preparing.
Add soup, milk and tuna.
Stir thoroughly.
Coat dish with butter and potato chips. Add tuna mixture, then top with potato chips and cheese strips.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mash. Add egg and mayonnaise.
Pour into a greased casserole. Cover with saltines and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly brown.

title: stuffed strawberries
directions: Dice 2 strawberries, set aside.
Cut a thin slice from stem end of each strawberry, forming a base for it to stand on.
Cut each strawberry into wedges.
Starting at the pointed end and cutting to, but not through the stem end.
Beat cream cheese with mixer until fluffy.
Stir in diced strawberries, pecans and powdered sugar.
Spoon or pipe about 1 tsp. of mixture into each strawberry.

title: southern squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and place in casserole dish.
Top with 1/4 stuffing mix that has been sauteed in a little butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Remove any excess pieces of fat from chicken.
Place chicken, giblets and neck in a skillet.
Add just enough water to cover. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until thickest pieces are tender, about 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: all american berries and cream
directions: In a small saucepan cook and stir apple jelly over medium heat until melted.
Cool.
Toss blueberries with half of the jelly.
On a large rectangular platter or tray, arrange blueberries in upper left hand corner in a square.
Place strawberries, stem side down in horizontal row (resembling a flag), leaving about 1 inch between each row for whipped cream filling.
With a pastry brush brush strawberries with remaining jelly.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt and cook until it forms a brittle ball when dropped into cold water.
Pour slowly over egg whites and beat until it loses gloss and holds shape.
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls or pour into greased pan.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, cocoa and water to a boil.
Add sugar, flour and soda.
Beat in sour cream, eggs and salt.
Cook at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix.
Roll to 1/3-inch thick.
Cut in shapes or squares.
Bake at 270° for about 20 minutes until just brown.

title: cappuchinno cream cheese brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter in a large microwaveable bowl on High 2 minutes or until butter is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: microwave fruit jam
directions: Microwave fruit on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in pectin.
Cook for another 2 minutes until bubbly.
Stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Test thickness and cook longer if not as desired.
Pour into shallow container to cool.
Pack in containers to freeze or eat right away.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, celery and onions until tender.
Add rest of ingredients except noodles.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle noodles on top and bake for 15 minutes.

title: fresh creamed corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Fry fat back in iron pan.
Put corn, water and salt and pepper in grease; cook slowly until it starts to cream.

title: hungarian crepes(palacsinta)
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Use a carefully cleaned nonstick pan.
Heat on high approximately 1/2 tablespoon oil and pour 1/2 cup of batter, spreading it evenly with quick and circular movements.
Lower heat to medium and turn over when it starts browning on the edges and detaches easily.
The palacsinta will be ready when it turns brown on the edges.
Makes 14 to 16.

title: lemon cheese pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and 8 ounces of the cream cheese. Add the 3 cups sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat well after each egg.
Add 4 teaspoons of the lemon flavoring.
Fold in flour.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Combine 1/4 flour with grated cheese and add to batter.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Place pan in cold oven.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door while cake is cooking.
Remove from oven and cool.
While cake is cooking, combine the powdered sugar, remaining cream cheese and flavoring.
Use enough evaporated milk to make icing of spreading consistency.
Beat well.
Frost cake when completely cooled.

title: chicken nuggets with a punch
directions: Cut chicken breasts into large chunks. Mix oil, garlic, and pepper with chicken pieces and marinate about 30 minutes. Combine breadcrumbs and cayenne pepper on a plate or shallow bowl. Roll chicken pieces in breadcrumbs and place on large cookie sheet in a single layer. Bake at 475° for about 15 minutes until browned and cooked through. For extra browning, broil for a few more minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix the yeast, dry milk, sugar and salt with 2 cups of flour. Add the water and mix well.
Add egg and cooking oil and beat until smooth.
Stir in the remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and satiny. Place the dough in a lightly oiled bowl and turn to coat completely.
Cover and let rise until doubled.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy saucepan, boil sugar, syrup, water, margarine and salt. Using candy thermometer, boil mixture to 265°. Add the Spanish peanuts. Boil until temperature reaches 302°. Remove from heat and add the soda. Stir well until soda dissolves. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Cool. Take handle of case knife and crack candy. Store in airtight container.

title: party pecan balls
directions: Cream 1/4 cup confectioners sugar and butter until smooth. Add vanilla; blend well.
Add flour and salt; blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, remove from broth. Reserve 2 cups chicken broth; chop chicken into small pieces and set aside. Cook and drain spaghetti, set aside. In a skillet, melt margarine and saute bell pepper, celery, and onion; add broth; simmer about 15 minutes. Add soups and simmer until well mixed; add chicken and spices; simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat; add spaghetti and mix. Place in a casserole dish and cover the top with cheese. Warm in oven or microwave until the cheese melts and serve hot. Delicious!

title: one skillet meal
directions: Batter and brown chicken in a skillet in 1/2 cup oil. Arrange chicken in a casserole dish.
Add ingredients in order of recipe, except cream of chicken soup.
Bake, covered, 35 to 40 minutes.
Add soup and bake until bubbling.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion into bowl.
Let stand for 10 minutes; drain well.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Drop by spoonful into oiled heated skillet. Cook over medium heat until brown on both sides.

title: pralines and brie
directions: Using a long, sharp knife, cut off and discard the top rind of the cheese.
Combine sugar, pecans or almonds and butter; mix well. Sprinkle evenly over the surface of the cheese.
Broil 6 inches from the source of heat, until topping is hot and bubbly.
Cool slightly.
Serve with sliced fruit, crackers or fresh bread. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: *This recipe is equally delicious with fresh raspberries and using raspberry Jell-O.

title: steak 'n potato dinner
directions: Cut steak into pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat meat with flour mixture.
In skillet, brown meat slowly in hot fat, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add broth.
Cover tightly; simmer for 30 minutes, until almost tender.
Place potatoes and onions over meat.
Cover tightly; cook slowly for 35 minutes, or until potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry nut casserole
directions: Layer ingredients as per the order they are given, in a clear loaf casserole dish.
Use 1/2 for the first layer and 1/2 for a second layer.
Pour melted butter over top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Let cool and add to dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl. Mix well, then add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy pecan cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in oil; add eggs.
Stir in sour cream; mix thoroughly until well blended.
In second bowl mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar mixture.
Add remaining batter.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave 10 minutes.
Top with glaze.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread one side of the tortilla with sour cream.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on the tortilla and roll up.
Fold under each end.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool, slice into 1 inch pieces to dip into salsa.

title: spicy cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Roll in bacon bits or bits and chives.
Form into desired shape.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add whole eggs one at a time at high speed.
Add flour at low speed.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: flax seed rolls(linfro rundstykker)
directions: Blend dry yeast in sifted white flour; add water, syrup and oil and mix well.
Blend salt, flax seed and whole wheat flour; add to yeast mixture and mix well.
(If too thin, add a little more white flour.)
Cover with a clean cloth and let rise until double, 30 to 40 minutes.
Put dough on a floured breadboard; divide in half and make 2 (6-inch long) rolls.
Cut each roll into 8 portions.
Form into 16 rolls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise again until doubled.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Combine French beans, stewed tomatoes and tomato wedges. Saute onion in butter.
Add mustard, horseradish, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Add to vegetables.
Cook, covered, 30 minutes in oven on 350°.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk.
Mix together flour, quick oats, light brown sugar, baking soda, salt and butter.
In a 9 x 9-inch baking pan, spread 3/4 of the crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Right out of the oven, sprinkle chocolate chips over hot crumb mixture, then pour melted caramel over chocolate chips.
Sprinkle rest of crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool in pan, then refrigerate overnight, then re-cut and remove from pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread uncooked ground beef (hamburger) on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Press lightly.
Next, press onion slices (rings) into meat.
Cover with the Tater Tots (45 to 50 of them).
Drizzle the soup mixed with the milk over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients in a colander and drain.
Bring to boil 3/4 cup sugar, 1/3 cup vinegar, 1/2 cup cooking oil, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 teaspoon celery seed. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: spicy shrimp gumbo
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper, celery, garlic, sausage, tomato sauce, broth, bay leaf and Cajun or Creole seasoning in a 2 1/2-quart pot, and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Dice chicken that was boiled to make broth. Heat broth over medium heat until boiling. Add all three types of corn; reduce heat to low and simmer until corn is tender. Add diced chicken, pepper, onion powder and parsley. Simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Add chopped eggs and serve.

title: spanish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well except cheese.
Put 1/2 of mixture into pan and spread cheese; then pour rest of mixture over cheese. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a pizza
pan with Pam.
Take cookie dough and press it out to your pan.
Put in oven.
Let it stay for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Mix softened cream cheese and 3/4 cup powdered sugar together.
Set aside.
Take cookie out and let cool.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cookie.
Take strawberries and cut them up along with kiwi and peaches (make sure peaches are drained).
Place fruit in a circular format around the cookie.
You're ready to eat.

title: las vegas hot beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cover with about 2 inches of water.
Add salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion flakes and bacon. Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil.
Add hot salsa, picante sauce, taco sauce and parsley if desired.
Stir real good.
Add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Can add catsup for color (1/2 cup).
Cook over low heat for 4 to 5 hours, until done.
Very good.

title: sesame fried chicken
directions: Rub chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine orange juice, garlic, ginger, sake (or white wine) and soy sauce.
Stir well. Place chicken in a shallow container and pour mixture over top. Cover and let stand at least 30 minutes until half day in the refrigerator.
Combine sesame seed, cornstarch and flour; stir well.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture, coating well.
Cook in hot oil until browned, turning to brown both sides.

title: fried cornmeal mush
directions: Mix the 1 cup water and other ingredients into the boiling water, stir and boil until mixture thickens.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Place in an oblong bread pan and refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Fry or deep fry until browned.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients, except nuts and cherries, together.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and cool slightly.
Add peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix and shape into balls.
Chill, if they are too soft, or insert toothpicks and refrigerate at least 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in top of a double broiler. (Keep hot.)
Dip each peanut butter ball. Put on wax paper or foil to dry.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: cape code portuguese fish chowder, 1954
directions: In deep kettle, fry pork cubes slowly, turning until only crisp pork bits remain.
Remove and save.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Chop 1 package of corned beef.
Mix with cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and Accent.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate overnight.
Roll with second package of chopped corned beef.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving juice.
In a large saucepan, combine clam juice, celery, onion and potatoes.
Add enough water to cover vegetables.
Cook over medium heat until tender (15 minutes). Combine milk and flour to make white sauce.
Cook over low heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add clams, undrained vegetables and sugar.
Heat 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: christmas candle salad
directions: Place a slice of pineapple on salad plate.
Stand a banana in the hole of pineapple. Top it with a cherry.
Put whipped cream or salad dressing around the banana at bottom on pineapple ring.

title: dottie's squash pickles
directions: Combine vinegar and seasoning.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill in covered bowl about 12 hours, stirring occasionally.
Good for salad or side dish.
Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: seashells and potatoes
directions: *Robert likes to cook crumbled sausage in the skillet first to add flavor and texture to this dish.
If you want to try this, decrease the amount of oil.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Dump in vanilla pudding and yellow cake mix; stir.
Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 2/3 cups cold water, lemon juice, sugar, vinegar, drained beets, pineapple with juice and nuts.
Mix well and chill.
When firm, add topping.

title: spicy raisin sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine raisins and water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir into raisins.
Cook for a minute, stirring.
Stir in spices, mustard and salt.
Cook, stirring, 3 to 5 minutes longer or until thickened.
Stir in vinegar and pecans.
Remove from heat. Spoon sauce over ham and garnish with fruit, if desired or serve raisin sauce on the side.
Quick and easy.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: safflower pastry
directions: In a medium bowl, place flour.
Add oil.
Stir with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Add 2 tablespoons water.
Stir until dough holds together, additional water only if needed.
Press firmly into a ball.
Sufficient pastry for 6 turnovers or a 9-inch pie shell.
Per portion, 136 calories, 0 mg cholesterol.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix lemon juice with mayonnaise. Combine all ingredients except pretzels in a large bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle crushed pretzels on top and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove and serve.
Entire recipe makes 8 servings.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Melt oleo and add sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Thaw frozen rolls, just enough to cut each roll in thirds.
Put in mixing bowl and pour oleo mixture over them.
Stir to coat the pieces of rolls.

title: sweet pickles(refrigerate)
directions: Add salt to cucumbers and onions; let stand 1 to 6 hours. Drain off juice.
Then add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Mix together and put in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add corn muffin mix to egg mixture, then add onion and pepper.
Put into a well-greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spread with sour cream and cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make a crust from these ingredients and put in a 9.5 x 13.5 x 2-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook meat until it changes color; drain off excess fat. Beat egg, then
add
remaining ingredients to egg mixture; mix well. Pour into
casserole
dish
sprayed
with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm in center.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Cook all ingredients except oil and food coloring to 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add oil and food coloring, stirring well.
Pour into a baking sheet covered in 10x sugar. Sprinkle top with sugar also.
As soon as it begins to harden a little, begin lifting at the corner.
Cut into bite size pieces with cooking shears or let cool completely and break apart with handle end of a butter knife.
Toss in more powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: nassau grits
directions: Fry bacon and remove from grease.
Use 1/4 cup of grease to saute onions and peppers.
Add tomatoes and ham.
Simmer one hour. Simmer grits and water one hour.
Combine the two and add bacon last.
Good with fish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli wild soup
directions: In large sauce pan, combine the water and rice mix with contents of seasoning packets.
Boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add soup, milk, cream cheese and salt. Stir until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and carrot; cook over medium heat for about 5-6 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender.
Garnish with almonds.

title: t's tatoe salad
directions: Boil potatoes, then peel.
Dice onion and celery; mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Add mayo, mustard and relish.
Mix well and top with hard-boiled eggs and paprika.

title: chicken and rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 14 to 15 minutes, stirring twice during cooking time.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: shredded cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add soup, water and rice.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Spread cabbage evenly in large flat casserole dish.
Spoon the meat mixture over. Do not stir.
Bake at 325° about 1 or 1-1/2 hours.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large pan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Put Ritz crackers in mixture and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Dot with butter.
Sprinkle crust of pie shell with mixture of apple pie spice, cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: okra onion casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 c. buttered breadcrumbs. Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with reserved buttered bread crumbs, and bake 5 additional minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Split down the center of each filet lengthwise.
Flatten slightly with meat mallet.
Brush strips with a little margarine and then trickle honey on each strip.
Sprinkle top with rosemary (preferably fresh).
Cover and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Each 1/2 filet feeds one person.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, melt the margarine over moderate heat.
Add the onion, celery and green pepper and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until the vegetables are soft.
Blend in the flour and paprika and cook, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in the chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens and comes to a boil, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the corn.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in the milk, lemon juice and black pepper; reduce the heat to low and heat the soup just to serving temperature, 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not boil or the mixture will curdle.
Serves 4.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; alternate flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Put in greased and floured pan.

title: old settler's beans
directions: Brown onion and meats.
Add sugar and catsup, then add kidney beans, lima beans and pork and beans.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 3-quart casserole one hour at 350°.

title: low calorie frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in small cups; freeze. Makes 25 cups (40 calories each).

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Chop pecans in blender, if available. Combine with flour, butter, granulated sugar, vanilla and salt. Mix with a fork or hands until well blended.
Gather in ball. With lightly floured hands, shape in 1-inch balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 20 minutes or until browned on bottom. Let cool slightly before removing from cookie sheets.
Put powdered sugar in a plastic bag and shake a few cookies at a a time until coated.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: silly salad
directions: Peel, core and cut up the apples. Cut up the cherries, grate carrots and open peaches.
Cut the apples in half, then cut one of the halves into 8 wedges. Cut each of the cherries into 4 quarters.
Drain the peaches.
Place a lettuce leaf on each of 8 plates, then a peach half, cut side down on each leaf.
Make
a silly face on the peach, using apple wedges for mouse ears, raisin eyes, chocolate chip nose and 2 pieces of cherry for mouth.
Use grated carrot for hair.
Place 4 marshmallows under each peach to make a necklace.
Serves 8.

title: kathy's lasagne(revised)
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to package (leave whole). Brown hamburger in skillet; drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer until hot.
Mix Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese together in large container.
Alternate layers of noodles, sauce and cheese in large rectangular casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and cook in oven at 450° for 45 minutes.
Will usually make 2 dishes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes for about 8 minutes.
Slice into wedges (leave skins on).
Place in casserole dish.
Cut margarine. Place around the potatoes; sprinkle steak seasoning, garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: duncan hines cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop by spoonfuls onto sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flour, soda and salt in very large bowl; add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Store in covered container and use as desired.
Batter will last 6 weeks in refrigerator!

title: sausi cheese bites
directions: Mix biscuit mix and sausage well.
Add cheese.
Mix well and form into balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and cook about 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve while hot.

title: chicken tenders on the grill
directions: Soak chicken tenders for 1 hour in Italian dressing in refrigerator.
Cover grill with foil and place slits in foil (for excess dressing to drip off).
Spoon dressing over tenders while cooking.
Cooking time is approximately 5 minutes on each side. The tenders will be white when done.

title: jello graham cracker pie
directions: Mix well and press into pie plate.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place bread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: Place cottage cheese on lettuce leaf on a plate. Arrange banana slices so they resemble a banana split. Set aside. Combine strawberries, peaches and pineapple in a bowl. Add Equal and mix. Spoon fruits onto cottage cheese.
Drizzle honey over top and sprinkle with coconut and top with cherry.

title: escalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Brown beef and add salt.
Alternate, in a buttered casserole, layers of potatoes, onion and meat.
Add seasoning to taste.

title: date nut rolls
directions: Cook sugar and milk together until it reaches 236° or soft ball stage.
Add dates and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts, salt and vanilla.
Cool for a few minutes, then beat until thick.
Form into 2 rolls in damp cloth.
Chill and slice.

title: macaroni salad
directions: I add celery seed and paprika.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix Ritz cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in remaining butter until clear, not brown.
Spoon into Ritz pie crust.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper.
Pour over onion.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until pie is firm.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Mix together chili sauce, crushed pineapple and brown sugar. Pour over kielbasa in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion sandwiches
directions: Mix and spread on white bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well.
The longer it sits, the better.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Chop the onion, bell pepper and celery into 1/2 inch pieces and put in a mixing bowl.
Add all other ingredients except honey and BBQ sauce.
Mix well.
In a separate dish, mix the honey and BBQ sauce together well.
Spray a loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Shape the meat mixture and place in the pan.
Spread half the BBQ and honey sauce on top of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Apply the rest of the sauce as a glaze and serve.

title: oven-fried chicken parmesan
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish and pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
This is very good with spaghetti sauce and noodles.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot pear juice.
Mix in pears and cream cheese.
Mixer or food processor can be used.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into large mold or 2 small molds.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken hoagie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Slice rolls lengthwise. Butter both sides and toast under broiler. Spread bottom half with chicken mixture.
Top with grated cheese. Garnish with green peppers and olives. Return to oven and broil until cheese is melted. Remove and top with other side of bread.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Pop popcorn; set aside.
Combine marshmallows, margarine and brown sugar in a medium mixing bowl.
Cook in microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Mix with popcorn and let set for a little while.

title: fiddlehead cake
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes, or when cooked.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and chili powder.
Set aside.
Line casserole with broken chips.
Add 1/2 of cut up chicken.
Pour 1/2 of mixture and grated cheese.
Crush next layer of chips fine, then add rest of chicken and rest of mixture.
Put a lot of cheese on top.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Put into a casserole dish (1 1/2-quart).
Spread soup over top.
Arrange Tater Tots on top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dieter's delite
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir. Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Generously grease and flour 12 muffin cups.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: quick stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems, fill cavity with sausage.
Broil or bake until sausage is cooked, about 5 to 8 minutes in 450° oven.
Quantity is an approximation, depends on size of mushrooms in the container.

title: tdy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Prepare macaroni and cheese as per package directions.
Mix meat, macaroni and cheese and soup in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until heated through or microwave 8 minutes on 80% power.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish. Mix milk and soup together and heat in saucepan.
Layer ingredients in casserole dish, starting with Tater Tots, corn, ground beef, cheese and half the soup.
End with cheese slices on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: syrian meat pies
directions: Prepare roll mix according to directions on box.
While dough is rising, mix other ingredients in bowl and let stand a short while.
Refrigerate until ready for it.
After dough has risen, pinch off enough to make 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Cover cookie sheet with wax paper or dish towel.
Place balls on cookie sheet, cover with another towel and let rise again.
Roll each ball into a circle about 4 inches in diameter.
Put 1 heaping tablespoonful meat mixture in center.
Bring up edges to center and seal.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until lightly browned.
Reheat when needed.

title: working mom's cookie dough
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Stir by hand until well blended.
Add 1 cup flour to cream cheese mixture, stirring by hand until dough forms a ball.
Knead in bowl or on floured surface 1 to 2 minutes, adding additional flour until smooth, pliable and not sticky.
(Dough is easier to shape the more it is handled.)
Shape or use cookie cutters to form cookies.

title: minestrone
directions: Mix beans and tomatoes in a large pot.
Add broth, spinach and orzo.
Bring to a boil, stirring to break up spinach.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until orzo is tender.
Makes 10 cups.

title: mike's snack
directions: Spread peanut butter on rice cake.
Top with honey and enjoy!

title: cherry coke jello salad
directions: Heat sugar and water to boiling point. Add pie filling and bring to boiling point again.
Pour over gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Add the rest of the ingredients, mixing well.
Chill until set in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green chile stew  (low sodium)
directions: Heat a large saucepan, add oil, and cook garlic until tender. Add pork cubes and cook and stir until no longer pink.
Add chipotle, chile and potatoes, and cover with water.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1 cup crushed soda crackers on top.
Drizzle 3 tablespoons butter over crackers and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Place flour in cup, then fill to 3/4 cup line with sugar.
Put in blender; add eggs.
Add evaporated milk, then add regular milk until it fills 2 cup line.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend all in blender.
Pour in one deep dish crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 350° for 20 minutes more.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Put ingredients into crock-pot and cook on low for about 6 hours.

title: mrs. greathouse's brownies
directions: By hand, mix sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Add 4 eggs and vanilla.
Add flour a little at a time.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes in a greased and floured pan.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and eggs.
Mix.
Add flour and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll in small balls.
Dip one side in sugar and put on baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tiny cream cheese biscuits
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed for two minutes or until creamy. Gradually add flour, beating at low speed just until blended.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and salt. Press into a large pan so that the candy will be about 1/2-inch thick.
Melt the chocolate over hot water; pour on top of candy. Cool; cut into square inches.
Makes about 36 pieces.

title: slippery finger paint
directions: Mix detergent and starch together till mixture is soft and damp throughout.
Add enough food coloring or paint to get the color you want.
If you put this paint on too thick, the paint chunks will fall off when dry.
When picture is dry, it may be sprayed with hair spray to keep paint from chipping.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts; stir well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet, or make into small balls. Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet.
Add salt and garlic powder. Set this aside.
Heat soup, milk and Velveeta until cheese is melted.
Add onion dip mix, green chiles and chopped pimento.
Set this aside.
Grate the Longhorn cheese and set it aside.
Soften tortillas in hot water (just dip the tortilla in the hot water and take it out quickly or it will come apart.)

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each one.
Add cocoa and mix.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: chocolate chip marble squares(yields two dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix butter, sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Beat in egg.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt; mix in walnuts.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops. slice potatoes and onions thin.
Heat soups (undiluted) to mix well.
Salt potatoes.
Line 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with onions.
Pour soup over.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chess squares
directions: Mix
cake
mix,
pudding,
margarine
and 2 eggs with a fork. Pat into a greased 10 x 14-inch baking pan.
Set aside. Mix
the powdered
sugar,
2 eggs, margarine and cream cheese with mixer. Pour
over	the
batter in pan and bake 1 hour or until golden brown at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: orange balls
directions: Put crushed vanilla wafers in bowl, then combine all ingredients except coconut.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls. Roll each ball in coconut and place on wax paper sheet until firm. Serves 18.
Will freeze well in freezer for 6 months if tightly sealed.

title: molasses cookies(old fashioned soft type)
directions: Mix all together well, except flour.
Add enough flour to make a soft, dull-looking dough.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out onto a floured board; cut out cookies (1/2-inch thick).
Sprinkle with sugar; bake at 375°.

title: lydia mummert's sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in buttermilk and add flour mixture, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake until golden brown.
These will be soft.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cheddar cheese, and garlic salt together.
Add hash browns.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with parmesan cheese and extra cheddar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: morning sparklers
directions: Combine mineral water and strawberry nectar in pitcher.
Serve over ice.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into greased, floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake is done.
Cool and top with this frosting.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into 11 x 15-inch cake pan.
Also dump the can of cherries and stir around to mix fruit.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt oleo and drip over cake mix, then sprinkle coconut and pecans over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Let cool and serve.

title: spice chiffon cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature. In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
In small bowl, sift together dry ingredients; add oil, water, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold batter into whites.
Turn into 10-inch ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes, or until done.
Cool upside-down on neck of bottle.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add mashed bananas and juices.
Mix well and freeze.
Defrost 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and nuts.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Put pie filling over crust.
Mix sour cream and egg yolk.
Space evenly over apples.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and put on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares.

title: yeast donuts
directions: Mix together; let rise 2 hours.
Roll out on floured board and cut with donut cutter.
Let rise 1 more hour and fry in deep hot fat.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon or plain sugar.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Gradually add flour and milk, stirring until it boils and thickens.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Let cool and split layers to make four.
Mix sugar and milk and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, marshmallows and coconut.
Beat well and spread between layers.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each.
Add lemon extract and blend.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or in a tube pan 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
I prefer to use a tube pan.
Needs to be made a week or so ahead.

title: bacon-cheese sizzlers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on party rye.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes until bubbly on top.

title: cheese-topped mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Fill each mushroom cap with about 1/2 teaspoon dressing.
Place mushrooms on broiler pan or cookie sheet.
Cut cheese into 1 x 1 x 1/4-inch slices; top each mushroom with cheese slice.
Heat broiler.
Broil mushrooms 5 to 6-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve immediately.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: black forest cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the dry cake mix with the remaining ingredients, mixing by hand or electric beater.
Pour batter evenly into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp; peel and
devein.	Cook
fish
with
small amount of water; drain.
Add fish and shrimp to other ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order given, drop by teaspoon and press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 or 9 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar into egg yolks. Add salt, stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture coats spoon. Cool. Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating into soft peaks. Add to custard and mix thoroughly. Add rum flavoring. Chill 3-4 hours. Pour into bowl, dot with whipped cream and nutmeg. Serves 6-8.

title: chinese pick-up sticks
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add soy sauce and Tabasco; mix well.
Place noodles in a bowl and drizzle sauce over them.
Toss to coat the noodles well.
Sprinkle with celery salt, onion powder and garlic powder and toss again.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well and shape.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in small amount of water until soft.
Add salt, pepper, milk and butter.
Heat until hot, but not boiling.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and serve.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: ziti with broccoli
directions: Saute margarine, onion and garlic.
Turn off heat; add 1/2 cup Italian dressing and 1/2 cup grated Parmesan and pour over ziti. Add cheese to taste.
Add broccoli.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together; fold into egg mixture, along with all remaining ingredients.
Drop by scant teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°. Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: icing for coconut cake
directions: Beat together sour cream and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Fold in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread on cake, sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Place chicken and bay leaf in a large Dutch oven and cover with salted water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour or until tender. Remove chicken and let cool.
Discard bay leaf.
Bone chicken and cut meat into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Reserve 1/4 cup chicken broth.
Set aside.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a pot.
Cook for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mountain lodge pancake syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; heat until sugar is dissolved.
(Do not boil.)
Serve hot.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Fold in blueberries; spread into 18-inch square pan. Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over batter. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield:
18 servings.

title: nutty canadian cheese block
directions: In medium bowl, blend cheeses with 2 tablespoons maple syrup. Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Shape into a rectangular block and brush with remaining 2 tablespoons maple syrup.
Roll in chopped pecans, or pat on with hands, coating cheese block evenly. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: tuna noodle casserole(double recipe)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Meanwhile in saucepan cook celery and onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour.
Stir in soup. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Carefully stir in tuna, pimiento and the noodles. Turn tuna mixture into 3 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top of mixture.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chew cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in flour.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Spread batter into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Cool.
Cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: onion-cheese dip mix
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Grind or chop in
blender
shrimp, onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Add
remaining
ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Fry in deep
hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: cinnamon raisin yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl. Add milk, butter, 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Stir with wooden spoon until smooth. Add remaining 1 cup flour and raisins. Stir vigorously 30 strokes or until the flour is mixed in. Batter will be stiff and sticky. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (10 to 15 minutes). Place batter in well-greased loaf pan. Spread evenly. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and cool on rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill. Makes 3 cups.

title: substitute for salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil noodles until done (break into 4 lengths before boiling). Rinse with cool water and drain well.
Add tomato, pepper and onion.
Pour in dressing and seasoning.
Stir well.
Chill before serving.

title: cavitini
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, sliced pepperoni, mushrooms and green pepper. Mix and pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle cheeses over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning mix in a large bowl until smooth.
Spread mixture into 13 x 9 pan or two 9-inch pie plates.
Spread taco sauce over mixture and then sprinkle cheese over top.
Dip with nacho chips and enjoy.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain fat.
Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour. Serve on buns.

title: colonial oatmeal bread
directions: About
hours
before
serving, or a day ahead:
In a large bowl, combine salt, yeast, 2 cups whole-wheat flour and 1 cup flour.
In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, heat water, honey and
butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
(Butter or margarine does not need to melt completely.) With mixer at low speed, gradually
beat liquid into dry ingredients just until blended. Increase
speed to medium; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Gradually beat in egg and
1 cup whole-wheat flour to make a thick batter;
continue beating
2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
With a wooden spoon, stir in oats, 1 cup whole
