wheat flour and 1 cup flour to make a soft dough.

title: microwave pineapple crumble
directions: Mix flour, sugar
and butter with a fork until crumbly. Remove 1 cup of
mixture
for topping and stir in cinnamon and reserve. Stir
baking powder into large crumb mixture.
Whisk egg with pineapple
juice
and mix lightly with crumb mixture. Lightly grease a
2-quart
round
dish
or Bundt pan.
Pour in mixture and top
with
reserved crumbs.
Microwave on Medium 8 minutes.
Turn dish and cook on High 2 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 baking pan. Mix sugar, flour and milk. Mix well, then add to melted margarine. Put fruit on top. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven or until done in center. Serve warm as is or with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: green beans in sweet vinaigrette
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan over low heat until jelly melts, stirring occasionally.
Wash beans, trim ends, remove strings and steam over boiling water for 11 minutes.
Add peppers; cover and steam 1 minute more.
Drain.
Transfer vegetables to bowl.
Spoon vinegar mixture over vegetables; toss.

title: crock-pot special
directions: In crock-pot layer beef, potatoes, onion and spices.
Pour soup mixed with milk over top.
Cover.
Cook all day while you are gone.
Great for singles or working moms.

title: chili soup
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until brown. Add all ingredients together until boiling. Also good for a slow cooker.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Sprinkle jello over fruit and stir. Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Prepare jumbo shells according to package directions; drain. Simmer tomato sauce, oregano, basil, onion powder, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir together the cheeses, chives and eggs.
Fill shells evenly with cheese mixture, about 1 tablespoonful.
Pour some sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour rest on top of shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart jar.
Put on lid and shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: hasty pudding
directions: Make a paste of the cornmeal and cold water, stirring frequently until there are no more lumps and pour gradually into the salted boiling water. Place in a double boiler and cook from 2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently to prevent burning. Serve hot with sugar and milk or as desired.

title: crustless cranberry pie
directions: Put cranberries in greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over them.
Spread nuts on top.
Bake eggs; add sugar and flour, beating well.
Add butter/oleo and shortening; beat well.
Pour over cranberries.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm.
Slices may be heated in microwave oven as needed.

title: blender pancakes
directions: Put wet ingredients in blender first.
Add dry ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Pour batter on lightly greased and hot griddle.

title: strawberry tall cake
directions: Bake
cake
according to package instructions for a two layer cake.
Cool
completely.
Slice
the layers in half and place in the freezer.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with assorted fruits.

title: broccoli and corn
directions: Combine broccoli, corn, onion, beaten egg and 1/2 cup of the cracker crumbs.
Put in a medium size baking dish.
Put 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: slaw
directions: Soak cabbage in cold water a while if you have time.
Add salt to enough water to cover cabbage.
Put over cabbage and let set 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally, squeeze out real dry and add pepper and onion. Measure sugar and vinegar.
Add to cabbage. This slaw will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: chutney mustard dressing
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, garlic, chutney and mustard in food processor.
While processing, gradually add olive oil.

title: sweet bread dough
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 2 cups flour. In 2-quart saucepan over low heat, slowly heat milk and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter does not need to melt. With mixer at low speed, gradually beat liquid into dry ingredients.
Increase speed to medium.
Beat 2 more minutes, occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Beat in eggs and 2 cups flour.
Continue beating 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour (about 4 1/4 cups) to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Shape into a ball.
Turn over in greased large bowl to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until dough is doubled, about 1 hour. Punch down dough.
On lightly floured surface, divide into pieces as recipes direct.
Cover and let rest for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and add soda, cinnamon, flour and carrots.
Makes 3 layers.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix 1 (3 1/4 ounce) package vanilla pudding (not instant), 1 1/2 cups fruit juice and 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pour over fruit that has been well drained.
Be sure bananas are well coated. Will keep for a week in refrigerator.

title: polish sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake covered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover and bake a little longer if needed.

title: broccoli, onion and raisin salad
directions: Cut broccoli in a large bowl. Dice onion and put into rings with broccoli. Add raisins. Cook bacon and crumble up over vegetables.

title: chicken and mushrooms in tarragon sauce(makes four 4-ounce servings)
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Saute chicken until brown, approximately 3 minutes per side.
Transfer chicken to a plate.
Add mushrooms, garlic and green onions to pan.
Saute until
mushrooms start to become soft.
Add wine, tarragon and lemon juice.
Return chicken to pan.
Add broth.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Cook and drain shrimp.
In a small amount of butter, cook onion.
Add sour cream and cream of shrimp soup.
Blend well. Stir in curry powder and shrimp.
Let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: peach bread pudding
directions: Dot
bread
with butter; toast slightly in oven.
Whisk eggs, sugar and milk.
Add peaches, then toasted bread.
Place in buttered,
sugared casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.

title: candied yams
directions: Place potatoes in casserole dish. Cover with sugar, salt and cinnamon. Dot with butter.
Sift flour over potatoes.
Add water. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove and cover with a layer of marshmallows. Return to oven to melt and brown marshmallows.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into buttered casserole.
Mix other ingredients in pan and heat until cheese melts.
Pour this over the potatoes in the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salted peanut chewies
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl until crumbly.
Spread mixture into large square pan sprayed with "Pam."
Press mixture evenly into the bottom of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes. Mixture will rise.
Remove cake mixture from oven and spread 3 cups of mini-marshmallows on top.
Bake for 3 minutes.
Marshmallows will puff; remove mixture from oven.

title: quick frozen fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, soften cream cheese.
Blend in sugar; stir in fruit.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Set out of freezer about 20 minutes before
serving.
Cut into squares
and serve on lettuce leaves.
Yield: 15 to 18 squares.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, salt, sugar and soda.
Heat liquids to 120° to 130°.
Add to dry ingredients; beat.
Stir in rest of flour.
Spoon into 2 greased pans.
Sprinkle tops with corn meal (optional).
(Will be sticky.)
Let rise 45 minutes in warm place.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: old-fashioned lemon crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff enough to roll and cut into squares.
Bake in flat pan.
Will keep several weeks if tightly covered.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in banana, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir into banana mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts.

title: baked sweet onions
directions: Set oven to 400.
Spray glass baking dish with Pam and layer onions.
Dot with butter and tuck rosemary in on layers.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and 1/2 parmesan cheese.
Add 1/2 cup water and cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: la pasada
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add tomatoes and soup.
Let simmer 10 minutes to distribute flavor.
Layer tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls, chill and then bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Combine milk, egg and oil; stir in flour and mix well.
Allow batter to stand 15 minutes.
Dip onion rings into batter.
Fry in deep fat until golden; drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt. Batter may also be used for chicken or shrimp.

title: hash-cheese biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: creamy potato salad(low-cal)
directions: Cook potatoes 25 minutes, until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel and cube and transfer to a large bowl.
Stir in celery, onion, green pepper, pimento and relish.

title: fresh peach ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into ice cream freezer and fill freezer with milk.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: chile cheese corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 9-inch cast-iron skillet or cake pan.
Cut cheese into slices approximately 1/4-inch thick. Slice peppers.
Combine corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn.
Melt butter.
Mix together eggs, sour cream and melted butter.
Pour egg mixture into corn meal mixture; stir until combined, but still lumpy.
Pour 1/2 the batter into prepared skillet.
Cover with cheese and peppers.
Pour remaining batter; bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Thaw potatoes for 1 hour.
Melt cheese in milk.
Add margarine, salt and onion, mixing well.
Pour over potatoes in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Chill for several hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: avocado salad
directions: Combine first 13 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Arrange salad greens on individual plates and top with avocado mixture. Garnish, if desired, with carambola slices.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: heavenly fluff salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water; add orange juice (frozen).
Then add fruit.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish; chill until set.
Spoon topping over top and serve.

title: watermelon sauce for pork chops, pork ribs or chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except watermelon, in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring occasionally.
Cool sauce and add pureed watermelon.
Use as a basting sauce for pork chops or chicken during cooking.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Add flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper; stir well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and Velveeta cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Add cream and stir until smooth. Stir in chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: In a bowl, whisk eggs and sugar until smooth. Add syrup, butter, vanilla, salt and pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: gravy train
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients until browned; drain well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with dressing mix, prepared wet. Spread soup over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until brown.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Drain meat and add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and noodles.

title: light bread(3 loaves or rolls)
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients.
Stir 3 cups of flour to mixture.
Let bubble (or rise), then work 7 cups flour in mixture.
Work 10 minutes.
Let rise again and make out loaves or rolls.
Bake at 350°.

title: flower pot cakes
directions: Note:
Need 10 flat bottom ice cream cones.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn into brown bag.
Combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in medium-size microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until mixture comes to a boil, stirring after every minute.
Microwave 2 minutes more.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Shake bag well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag well.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes more.
Shake bag well.
Pour out into large cookie sheet until it cools, stirring to keep it separated.

title: no-fat fruit dip
directions: Stir together and refrigerate.
Serve with sliced fresh fruit.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: You will need round toothpicks.

title: jo's original super homemade chili
directions: Use iron skillet and brown ground beef, salt, pepper, garlic, onion and chili powder.
Cover bottom of skillet with salt (no grease).
Stir in sausage, bacon and seasoning mix.
Add sauces, tomatoes and beans.
Stir well, until tomatoes are chunky throughout mixture.
Cook slowly for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add several slices of American cheese.
Simmer as long as you like. Serve with breaded cheese sticks or crackers.

title: deluxe egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 cup or enough for 3 to 4 sandwiches or a spread for crackers.

title: ham salad spread
directions: Grind bologna and add relish, Miracle Whip, onion, salt and pepper.
Add sugar to taste.
Mix well. Cool.
Mix again before serving.

title: mama's poor folks apple pie
directions: Slice biscuits twice.
(Save center slice for top of pie.) Arrange bottom layer of biscuits into dish and cover with apple mixture.
Add next layer of biscuits and apple mixture.
Put third layer of biscuits and top with apple mixture.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Prepare medium shells according to package instructions and drain.
In small bowl, blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add yogurt mixture; toss to coat.
Cover.
Chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with box of yellow cake mix.
Cover with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Pour 3/4 cup melted butter over all. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Cut into small strips the peeled watermelon rind.
Soak overnight in sugar.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into hot jars. Seal and store until ready to eat.

title: date oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening add sugar until fluffy.
Blend in eggs, milk, and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees.

title: sandy's apple dip
directions: Cream first 4 items together. Add peanuts to mixture. Refrigerate. Serve with Granny Smith apples that have been sliced and dipped in cool ice water with lemon juice.

title: beef paprika
directions: Place roast in baking dish.
Put 1 package of Lipton dried onion soup in with the roast.
Add water and black pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 325° oven until done.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Slice steak in 1/4-inch strips.
Put in Ziploc bag.
Combine 1/4 cup water, Worcestershire sauce, garlic cloves and seasoned salt.
Pour over steak and marinate in refrigerator 2 to 4 hours, turning bag occasionally.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving marinade.
Coat a wok or nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Place over medium high heat until hot.
Add steak and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, pepper and onions.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Add green beans and fry 1 minute.
Combine cornstarch, marinade and 1 1/2 teaspoons water.
Add to steak mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thick and thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
The last 5 to 10 minutes, add cashews.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Place rice in buttered baking dish.
Spread half the onions and cheese over the rice.
Heat chili and pour over rice.
Top with remaining cheese, onions and crushed corn chips.
Heat in 375° oven for about 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix together; chill and serve.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons in a cup.
Fill with boiling water; stir well.
Serves 50.
Great as a Christmas gift when put in jars.

title: chili dip
directions: Saute onion and ground beef.
Drain off any liquid.
Add seasonings to taste.
Mash the refried beans into the meat mixture. Add catsup and Pico Pico sauce to taste.
Simmer at least 1 hour. Add more seasonings as needed.
Top with cheese before serving.

title: potato refrigerator dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups of the flour.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough; knead until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or dough can be kept for 5 days.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours before baking.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until done.
Cut into cubes in a casserole dish.
Mix milk and soup together and pour over chicken. Add broccoli.
Layer the top with Cheddar cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: walnut rum raisin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a small bowl, combine raisins and water.
Set aside.
Combine crumbs, walnuts, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan or a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Drain water from raisins.
Stir rum flavoring in batter. Pour into prepared pan.
Top evenly with raisins.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Top with Walnut Praline Glaze. Chill.
Refrigerate.

title: evelyn's sweet pickle relish
directions: Drain ground pickles.
Grind peppers and onions.
Mix together. Work in salt and let stand 4 hours.
Add rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil and can.
Can be divided to make smaller amounts.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well until well blended.
Let stand for 2 hours
in
refrigerator.
Make
into
small balls.
Put cookies on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork. Bake at 350° until brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: italian style green beans
directions: *One-fourth
teaspoon each oregano, marjoram, basil and 1/8 teaspoon
rubbed sage can be substituted for 3/4 teaspoon Italian seasoning.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix by hand.
(Do Not Beat!) Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees
for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack.

title: elegant salad
directions: Mix together. Before serving, add 1 cup mayonnaise, mixed with 1 cup sugar and 1 Tbsp. vinegar.

title: easy tarts
directions: Put vanilla wafer in cupcake paper.
Add a small dab of butter or oleo
on
top
of
wafer.
Mix
cream
cheese, lemon juice, vanilla, sugar
and egg until smooth.
Spoon mixture on top of wafer and
butter or oleo until cupcake paper 1/2 full. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool slightly. Spoon 1 tablespoon
of
cherry
pie
filling
on top of cooked tart.

title: bethany's peanut butter pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar, salt, corn syrup, peanut butter and eggs.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake until crust is golden brown, about 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly and refrigerate.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Mix eggs, milk and oil;
gradually add to flour,
beating	until smooth.
Dip pieces of cauliflower into batter and fry
in	oil
until golden brown on all sides.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Add milk and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend together. Fold in blueberries.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: meatballs with burgundy sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix
all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in
ungreased	jelly
roll
pan until done (about 10 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.

title: easy chip dip
directions: Put the cream cheese in a bowl and soften up with a spoon. Gradually add sauce, mixing well after each addition.

title: turkey strata
directions: Butter two 9 x 12-inch pans.
Line with bread.
Layer with chicken, mushrooms and chestnuts.
Dot with mayonnaise.
Combine soups and pour over top.
Sprinkle 2 ounce can of pimento (optional).
Put 11 slices of cheese on top.
Mix together eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can place buttered croutons on top before baking.

title: cheese daisies
directions: Cream butter and cheese (with hand).
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Roll pastry into long roll and wrap in waxed paper. Refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour or freeze.
Cut into slices (1/3-inch for olives and cocktail sausages).

For sausages, press with heel of hand into elongated oval and wrap around sausage. For olives (large ones are best), press pastry slice into cup shape and wrap around olive, leaving pimiento end exposed.
The original recipe suggests pressing a pecan half into each slice.

title: dried apple stackcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Beat in molasses.
Add soda to buttermilk; stir well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Mix well.
Pour batter in round pans that have been greased and floured, using 1 cup batter to each pan.
(This amount of batter will make 8 layers in 8-inch pans and 6 layers for 9-inch pans.) Batter will keep well if covered with waxed paper until all the layers are baked.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool on rack before removing from the pans.

title: squash or broccoli casserole
directions: Cook squash or broccoli and drain.
In a large bowl, mix mayonnaise, cheese, cream of mushroom soup and onion.
Beat eggs and add to this mixture.
Mix in squash or broccoli and pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until center is set.

title: not too rich broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender. Arrange in baking dish. Add lemon juice gradually to the mayonnaise, stirring constantly. Drizzle over broccoli. Top with cheese slices.
Place, uncovered, in a 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except crushed potato chips.
Pour into casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: red potato casserole
directions: Cook bacon.
Drain.
Reserve fat and crumble.
Boil 2 quarts water.
Blanch potatoes and beans together for just 2 minutes. Drain well and place in large mixing bowl.
Add reserved bacon fat to potatoes and beans and toss.
(Should be 3 tablespoons.
Add oil to equal if not enough.)
Add onion, mushrooms, cheese, dill, salt and pepper along with crumbled bacon and combine.
Turn into greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: trash(a hot variety of party mix)
directions: Pretzels and Cheerios are optional.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Heat sugar, unsweetened chocolate and Carnation until chocolate melts and ingredients come to a boil.
Boil for 15 to 18 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add margarine, peanut butter, marshmallow cream and chopped walnuts.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pans.
Cut when warm for best results.

title: cape cod cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread half the cranberries in the bottom of a well greased 10-inch pie plate.
Spread the nuts over the cranberries.
Add the sugar to the eggs, beating well.
Beat in the flour, butter and shortening.
Pour over the cranberries and nuts.
Top off with remaining cranberries.
Bake about 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: pecan-oatmeal cake
directions: In large bowl, place oats, margarine and boiling water.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Stir in both sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Turn into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate cake with sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: meatballs, rice and potatoes
directions: Roll hamburger into small to medium balls.
Cut potatoes into cubes; place in large roasting pan.
Add rice and onion.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup mix, pepper and salt over meatballs, potatoes and rice.
Add 1 cup water to cream of chicken soup; pour over meatballs, potatoes and rice.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown meat, onion and taco seasoning; drain.
Add tomato sauce and refried beans.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Add sour cream on top of hamburger mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese bubbles at 350°.

title: yummy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
In another bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Combine both mixtures together a little at a time, until all is blended.
Roll into small balls and put on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and remove from cookie sheet.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Pour first 7 ingredients into crock pot.
Cook on low until heated and cream cheese is melted.
Pour into bowls and top with chips and cheese.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Spread half of mixture on bottom of pan; press.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar, milk and Dream Whip.
Beat until stiff.
Pour half of Dream Whip mixture on top of graham cracker mixture, then add all of the cherry pie filling.
Top with another layer of Dream Whip mixture and sprinkle remaining graham cracker crumbs over all.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Cream the next 3 ingredients for 15 minutes and pour into crust.
Top with bananas. Cover that with pineapple. Top with Cool Whip.
You can put cherries, walnuts or chocolate syrup on top.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours. Good to make the night before serving.

title: ooey gooey chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
While cake is warm, punch holes in it.
Pour Eagle Brand cream in holes and then pour caramel topping in holes.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and top with crushed candy bars.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add 8 cups marshmallows mix all together very pretty salad.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour 1/4 of batter in each small bread pan. Mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Sprinkle 1/4 on each loaf.
Pour in rest of batter.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: egg and ham casserole(prepared the evening before)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line the pan with bread or croutons. Add in layers, Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, ham, Swiss cheese and onion.
Mix eggs, milk, half and half and dried mustard. Pour this mixture over all layered ingredients in a pan.
Place in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Simmer for 10 minutes, do not drain.
Make white sauce and add to vegetables.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mixture over nuts and coconut.
Cream together the cream cheese, oleo, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cake mixture. Do not spread.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: easy burritos(makes about 12 burritos)
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients simmer until warm, about 10 minutes.
Heat flour tortillas on griddle.
Place mix on tortilla. Add remaining ingredients.
Roll tightly and eat with your hands. Could be messy.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream butter and add sugar and salt.
Pour hot water over mixture and stir.
When dissolved, add egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Place in refrigerator at least 8 hours before using.
Lightly knead and shape into rolls; allow to rise about 45 minutes.
Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: low-fat fudge brownie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9-inch baking pan with nonfat cooking spray (PAM). Combine cream cheese and sugar until well blended and creamy. Add vanilla, salt and eggs; beat well. Add cocoa, baking powder and flour, mixing until smooth. Finally, add the sour cream (the magic ingredient to soft chewy brownies). Blend by hand. Add chocolate chips for the deluxe version. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes. DO NOT OVERBAKE! Use the toothpick test if you are not sure the brownies are done. Stick the toothpick in the middle and if it comes out clean, the brownies are done. Enjoy them with a friend or eat them on your own.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese into bottom of 9-inch round cake pan. Rinse black beans well, and drain.
Spread beans over cream cheese.
Drain RoTel, layer onto beans.
Cover well with grated cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted and dip is warmed through.
Eat with triscuits or corn chips.

title: milk chocolate florentines
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, sugar, flour, corn syrup, milk, vanilla extract and salt; mix well.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls, about 3 inches apart, onto foil-lined cookie sheets. Spread thin with a rubber spatula.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool completely on wire racks.
Peel foil from cookies. Melt over hot (not boiling) water, the milk chocolate morsels; stir until smooth.
Spread chocolate on flat side of 1/2 the cookies. Top with remaining cookies.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen sandwich cookies.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the cheese and mix to a batter with the melted shortening, beaten egg and milk.
Turn into hot, well-greased muffin pans and bake in a moderately hot oven for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs 4 to 5 minutes.
Add sugars, vanilla and butter, mixing thoroughly to combine.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and melted butter; pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks butter and powdered sugar for 15 minutes.
Spread over unbaked crust, sliced bananas and pineapple. Add whipped topping.
Top with cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Saute onions, bacon and ground beef until meat loses its redness.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients.
Stir.
Bake in Dutch oven or large casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours (heats up great).

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients except lemon slices in saucepan.
Stir over heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Serve at once.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Yields 8 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a very large bowl (4 to 5-quart).
Pour over the boiling water; stir to combine.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water; mix both together.
Stir in 5 cups white flour.
Knead dough, in bowl, for approximately 10 minutes, adding flour as needed.
Place dough in covered, greased bowl; let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down; shape into 2 loaves. Place in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack on side; brush with margarine for a soft crust.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Pour hot cooked (according to directions) pudding into dry cake mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Cook 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sand dollar cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal and garlic salt in medium bowl and add water, stirring to a thin consistency, but not too thin.
In a frying pan, medium to high heat, using a tablespoon, spoon mixture into hot cooking oil (not deep).
Each patty should spread to about 3-inches round.
Fry until golden brown and crispy around the edges, turning with spatula.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: crispy bacon shrimp
directions: In shrimp are frozen, thaw on paper toweling to absorb moisture.
Combine all remaining ingredients except bacon.
When shrimp are completely defrosted, pour marinade over them.
Let shrimp marinate in refrigerate several hours.
Drain.
Wrap each shrimp in bacon and secure with toothpick.
Broil until shrimp are pink and bacon crisp.
When serving, replace burnt toothpicks with fresh ones.
Yields 6 appetizer servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Blend together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine and add beaten egg, milk, melted butter. Add blueberries, stir in easy. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Melt butter.
Cream with sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and mashed beans; mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake for about 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: chad's favorite lemon pound cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each egg.
Alternately mix flour and milk to creamed mixture.
Add lemon and vanilla flavorings.
Mix well.
Put in cold oven and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil. Add peanuts.
Stir constantly until peanuts are well coated and mixture becomes dry.
Place coated peanuts on a large baking sheet, separate them well.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: turkey barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: "straight a" norwegian apple kake
directions: Grease 9-inch spring-form pan and set oven at 350°.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs, flour and baking powder. Mix with hands to form a ball of dough.
Dough will be stiff.
Chill dough about 15 minutes before rolling out.
Roll chilled dough into a circle large enough to fit the bottom of the spring-form pan and 1/4 up sides of pan.
(Save remaining dough.)
Line pan with dough.
Fill with cooked apples.

title: pineapple bisque
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Line a 14 x 16-inch pan with half the wafer crumbs.
Spread beaten mixture on this.
Add layer of pineapple.
Add chopped cherries.
Spread whipped cream evenly. Sprinkle with nuts.
Add remainder of crushed wafers as crust. Chill 12 hours.

title: dinner rolls italiano
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and seasonings.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and 2 tablespoons butter until warm (butter does not need to melt).
Add heated liquids to flour mixture.
Add egg.
Blend with mixer at low speed until moistened; beat three minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in 1/2 cup cheese and enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on well floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: granny thrift's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco, then add sugar and beat until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time.
After this is creamed, add 1/2 of the milk and beat well.
Then add the vanilla, half of the flour and the baking powder.
Beat well.
Then add the rest of the milk.
Beat well and then add the remaining flour and beat until it is well blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
You should let all of your ingredients get to room temperature for best results.

title: lemon lime punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as on package; add pineapple juice, apple juice and orange juice.
Shake well.
Add ginger ale and stir right before serving.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse with cold water.
Add other ingredients; mix well with mayonnaise to taste.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: jambalaya mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix well.
Heat for 15 minutes at 375°.
Stir and serve with crackers, vegetables, etc.

title: spicy crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place the mushroom caps on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
In a large bowl, combine the crab meat, garlic, jalapenos, Pepper Jack, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, salt, mayonnaise and Parmagiano-Reggiano.
Place a heaping tablespoon of the crab mixture into the cap of each mushroom.
Bake the mushroom caps for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with grilled radicchio.
Yield: 8 appetizer servings.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly and make a thin layer of graham crackers across bottom of pan.
Add coconut, nuts, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour milk evenly over everything.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until chips start to melt.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: vegetable sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on sandwich slices.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook altogether 30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: simple cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, condensed milk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 1 hour.
Top with cherry topping.

title: savory stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash squash thoroughly; cook in boiling, salted water 5 minutes.
Cut squash in half lengthwise; scoop out and discard seeds.
Sprinkle cavities with salt and pepper; set aside.

title: stir-fry chicken with almonds
directions: Stir broth, soy sauce and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat oil over high heat.
Add almonds.
Stir-fry one minute until brown.
Remove. Add chicken; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove.
Add green onions and pea pods; stir-fry 1 minute.
Remove.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute.
Put everything back in pan with broth mixture. Stir until bubbly.
Cover; cook 1 minute.
Stir in almonds last.

title: classic italian chicken salad
directions: Toss salad greens with chicken breast strips, tomatoes, and onions in large salad bowl.
Add dressing; mix lightly.
Top with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding, Tang and juice of pineapple.
Mix with fruit and chill.

title: hot dill carrot strips
directions: In large pot, bring to boil 3 quarts water, vinegar and 1 cup salt.
Simmer for 20 minutes for a good brine.
Wash and sterilize 8 pint jars.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Thoroughly combine biscuit mix, sugar and spices.
Combine milk, pumpkin, egg and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients until blended.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter pan.
Line pan with bread slices.
Spread chicken over bread.
Spread mushrooms, then sliced water chestnuts over other and dot with mayonnaise.

title: simply strawberry - strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil in a bowl.
Dissolve jello in the 1/2 cup warm water and add to mixture along with 1/2 the strawberries.
Bake according to cake mix box directions until cake is done.
While cake bakes, prepare frosting.

title: garbanzo cheese
directions: A bit of celery seed or caraway seed adds a nice flavor.

title: raspberry and tomato jelly
directions: Boil tomatoes for 1/2 hour.
Add sugar to tomatoes; boil for 3 minutes.
Take off fire.
Add the jello; mix.
Put in 6 jars.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix together.
Press in graham cracker
box lined with Reynolds Wrap.
Put pecans and cherries on top of it.

title: no bake pumpkin pie
directions: Brown coconut with margarine (light golden brown).
Mix pumpkin and instant pudding and Cool Whip; place 3/4 coconut (browned) into each of the crusts.
Pour pumpkin mixture over coconut, then garnish pies with the remainder of coconut.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges, coconut and marshmallows in mixing bowl.
Stir in enough sour cream to moisten well.
Chill before serving.

title: deep dish golden apple pie
directions: Core and thinly slice apples to equal 7 cups.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Stir in apples, raisins and orange juice. Place in 2-inch deep 9-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry to 11-inch diameter; adjust over apples.
Tuck in edges and flute, pulling points of fluting over side of dish to secure crust.
Decorate with apple-shaped pastry cutouts if desired.
Cut vents.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until crust is golden and filling is steaming.
If necessary, cover partway through baking to prevent browning.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper until tender.
Drain water and mash.
Add milk, cheese, butter, eggs and crackers; stir together.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: kahlua(coffee liqueur)
directions: Combine coffee, water and sugar.
Stir until dissolved; let cool.
Add brandy.
Pour into 2 bottles.
Cut vanilla bean into quarters.
Add 1/2 bean to each bottle.
Age in dark, cool place for at least 1 month.

title: kirkland's 3 minute dessert
directions: A quick and easy dessert that children can do by themselves.

title: minted lamb stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Use a spoon to remove pulp from center of each half, enough to make about 3/4 cup finely diced raw eggplant.
Combine diced eggplant with remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and cheese.

Spoon filling into eggplant halves, spreading it with tines of a fork so that all the cut surface of the eggplant halves are covered with filling. Sprinkle filling lightly with bread crumbs and cheese.
Arrange halves, filled side up, in a shallow nonstick baking dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Cook green beans as per directions and drain water.
Add mushroom soup, cheese, almonds, milk and HALF the onion rings. Mix well and then place in a greased casserole or baking dish. Place in refrigerator over night.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: spinach fandango
directions: Brown beef, onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano; add salt and pepper.
Top with frozen spinach; cover.
Steam until spinach separates.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Cover spinach. Heat until warmed.
Garnish with cheese.
Steam until melted. Serves 6.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and milk in saucepan.
Cook until mixture turns slightly brown and forms a soft but firm ball when tested in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture cools and begins to thicken slightly.
Add the dates and nuts.
Roll out on wax paper, forming a long roll.
Roll in a small amount of powdered sugar.
Place in refrigerator until solid, then slice in thin slices.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, cream cheese and sugar; chill.
Use lemon juice to keep the apples from turning brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl large enough to hold it. Blend well and refrigerate for at least 8 hours before using. Serve with chips or assorted fresh vegetable crunchies.

title: dad's cookies
directions: Cream margarine; add sugars and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: In a bowl, stir together cream cheese, garlic salt, pepper and sour cream until smooth.
Set aside.
Prepare and boil quartered potatoes.
Drain.
Mash potatoes into fine lumps.
Add sour cream mixture to potatoes while beating.
Spoon potatoes into a well buttered shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Add dot of butter and paprika.
Bake, covered in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover. Bake 10 more minutes until top is golden brown.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
(Can be made day before.
Keep refrigerated.
Bake 50 minutes if refrigerated.)

title: miracle cookies
directions: Using a fork, cream together peanut butter and sugar.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Roll dough in 3/4-inch balls.
Put on ungreased pan. Flatten with a fork.
Bake cookies in a preheated oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool, then take off of cookie sheets.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 8 minutes.
Drain salt and pepper and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up butter over noodles.
Mix together beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over noodles and cheese.
Bake, covered with foil, at 375° for 30 minutes. This can be halved for a small crowd or "one an a halved" for a larger crowd.

title: corn casserole
directions: Single recipe (multiply by 3 for standard cafeteria pans).

title: baked-fried chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese and garlic in a bowl.
Brush chicken pieces with melted margarine, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: best ever peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbs form. Spread on bottom of pie crust, save a small amount to sprinkle on top of the pie.
Prepare pudding with 1-3/4 cups milk.
Pour in pie shell on top of peanut butter mixture.
Let set a few minutes. Put cool whip on top of pudding and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy mocha fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square baking pan with aluminum foil; set aside. In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, milk, marshmallow cream, butter, coffee liqueur and instant coffee.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: husband's cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add tomato soup and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Using greased and floured tube pan, bake in moderate 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in microwave; add onion to butter and microwave for 3 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Add cheese, soup and milk and microwave until cheese is melted.
Place broccoli and rice in casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli and rice.
Stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Enjoy.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients (dry).
Add milk slowly.
Cook over low heat until thick. Add butter and vanilla.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix
fruit with 1 cup sugar (if using pie filling, omit sugar).
Put
butter
in deep pan or casserole and set in 350° oven
to
melt.
Stir
up
batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, salt, baking
powder
and
milk.	Pour
over
melted butter.
Do not stir.
Put fruit on top.
Bake 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
Batter rises to top during baking.	Bake at 350°.
Top with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter; saute the celery and onion.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth and milk.
Stir until thickened. Add rice and chicken.

title: hungarian or banana peppers
directions: Thoroughly wash peppers.
Cut in small slices (circles).
Put peppers in a brine made of 1 gallon water to 2 cups of salt. Weight to hold peppers under brine.
Next day, drain well and pack peppers into sterilized jars.
Make a pickling solution of 1 gallon water, 1 cup salt, 1 cup vinegar, 1 clove garlic, 1 grape leaf and dill bunch.
Bring to boil.
Pour over peppers to within 1/2-inch of top.
Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables together.
Mix milk, mayonnaise, sugar, pepper and salt.
Pour everything over cooled macaroni and mix well.
Make a day before serving.

title: holiday cranberry relish
directions: Cut orange into 4 pieces. Remove seeds. Position knife blade in food processor bowl. Add orange and process until finely chopped.
Transfer to a nonaluminum bowl and set aside.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix together ingredients except whipped cream or Cool Whip. Cook until thickened.
(Can be prepared a day ahead.)
Chill. Before serving, fold in 1 cup whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix drained carrots, sugar, eggs, flour and baking powder well.
Add in melted margarine and cinnamon.
Pour into a greased pan or dish and bake for one hour at 325°.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Brown diced onion in chicken broth.
Add cooked ground turkey. Stir refried beans into turkey mixture.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle green chilies over top of turkey-bean mixture.
Spread 1/2 of cheese over this.
Pour taco sauce over cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and spoon sour cream to make a cross on top of casserole.
Serve with chips.

title: orange raisin cole slaw
directions: Drain orange sections, reserve 1/4 cup juice.
Combine orange sections, cabbage and raisins.
Blend mayonnaise, salt, sugar, celery seed and orange juice.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Toss lightly.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
In a separate bowl, beat together sugar, zucchini and eggs.
Add oil and lemon peel to wet mixture and mix well. Stir in flour mixture.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
(Enough for 3 layers in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.)
Brown ground beef and mushrooms.
Drain.
Add jar of spaghetti sauce and heat in skillet until hot.
Layer in baking dish, beginning with meat sauce first, followed by a layer of noodles, Mozzarella cheese (alternate with Swiss cheese) and sprinkled with Parmesan.
Continue to layer until pan is full, topping with either Swiss or Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into small to medium balls and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a bowl, sift first 5 ingredients together. Beat together next 5 ingredients, in a separate bowl, mix all ingredients together.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
In large bowl, mix together margarine, 10x sugar, eggs and hot water.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute chopped vegetables in butter until soft.
In large pot, brown beef and sausage and add bacon.
Cook until meat is blanched.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add vegetable mixture to meat mixture; cook 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Add rice, using small amount at a time; don't make dressing runny.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°, uncovered.

title: honey carrots
directions: Wash and trim carrots.
Cook in a small amount of boiling salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine in a skillet or saucepan.
Add sugar, honey and carrots. Cook over low heat, turning carrots frequently until well glazed. Serve immediately.

title: dump cake
directions: Into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, put the pineapple, pie filling and cake mix in that order, sprinkling the dry cake mix over all. Do not mix.
Sprinkle with walnuts and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: dressing balls
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add celery and onion; cook until tender.
Add to dressing mix along with egg and 1 can chicken broth.
Form this into balls.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: hotter 'n hell chili
directions: Brown ground beef and season with salt and chili pepper.
Drain beans and beef; mix with onions and tomatoes.
Add 4 to 6 dried chili peppers, ketchup (1/2 cup), garlic salt to taste and cayenne pepper and black pepper to taste.
Cook for about an hour on low, stirring frequently.
I also add additional chili powder (I like it hot).
Just before ready to serve, add tablespoon cumin and mustard.
Serve with Fritos, grated Cheddar cheese, jalapenos (sliced) or Mexican corn bread.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Into 1 quart water, add clams, clam juice, tomatoes, peppers, onions and celery.
Cook 1 hour.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Combine mix and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it boils.
Stir constantly.
Add cheese.
Continue cooking; beat until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into lightly oiled 1-quart mold.
Place wax paper on surface; chill until firm. Unmold.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: 7 minute frosting
directions: Stir unbeaten egg white, sugar and cold water on top of a double boiler.
Place over boiling water and beat 7 minutes. Remove from burner and
add
teaspoon	of
vanilla;
beat until nearly cold and add baking powder.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients into rice.
Top with pieces of cut up chicken.
Dust with paprika for color.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover to brown for a few minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions and pepper in large skillet.
Add chili powder, tomatoes, tomato paste, olives, noodles, Worcestershire sauce, creamed corn and tomato sauce.
Mix and place in greased casserole.
Cover with grated cheese and bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Will serve about 12 people.

title: annie's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix crumbled cornbread, stuffing mix, butter, celery and onion.
Add sage, poultry seasoning, black pepper and salt to tate.
Stir while pouring 2 cups or more of turkey broth into dressing until moistened to taste.
Amount of liquid may vary. Bake at 350°.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well and divide into two balls. Roll out into two circles and line pie pans. Use as needed.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Thaw the Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Sprinkle in the pudding (dry).
Drain 1 can of pineapple but don't drain the other.
Add both cans to mixture.
Stir until green.
Then add marshmallows and stir.
Then sprinkle in the nuts and refrigerate to keep cool.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Empty can of cherries into baking dish; sprinkle cake mix over the cherries; melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Bake in oven at least 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for ease in cutting; serve as is or top with ice cream or whipped cream.
(Other fruit may be substituted for cherries.)

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, in ungreased pan 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Place potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in pan.
Dot with butter.
Add ham strips.
Continue with layers.
At last, add milk.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/4 hours.

title: surprise meringues
directions: Beat together egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition until peaks become stiff.
Fold in chocolate pieces and nuts. Drop from teaspoons on piece of brown paper placed on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: oriental shrimp and snow peas express
directions: Combine Marsala wine, teriyaki sauce, salt and pepper; set sauce aside.
Butterfly shrimp by slitting lengthwise without cutting through.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over high heat.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Transfer shrimp to a platter.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil. Add scallions
and stir for 1 minute.
Add sauce, snow peas, ginger and garlic; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation Time:
5 minutes.
Cooking Time:
6 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: I double the topping mixture because I like the crunchies!

title: banana tart
directions: Mix flour and melted butter into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 to 18 minutes until light brown.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on top of baked crust.
Slice bananas on top of cream cheese layer.
Mix pudding per directions and spread on top of bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding eggs one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and blend well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti as usual; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Cut cucumbers, onion and tomato into medium pieces in a large bowl.
Mix in spaghetti and Salad Delight (seasoned to taste).
Add Italian dressing.
Shake well before adding.
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Blend together, flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add raisins and caraway seeds.
Beat eggs and milk in a separate bowl.
Add to dry ingredients,
Mix well.
Pour into well greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill overnight.
Add additional salad dressing just before serving.

title: oh my gosh!
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cook until heated through.
Serve over toast.

title: mary joiner's chocolate layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add flour mixture and milk.
Alternate, beginning with flour and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Makes 8 to 10 layers.
Put 4 tablespoon of batter to each pan.
Bake, but just until layers are dry, but not brown.
Ice with Chocolate Icing.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt the butter and chocolate in a large saucepan.
Then add the sugar, flour, baking powder, nuts and vanilla to the butter and chocolate.
Beat the 2 eggs in, one at a time.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible zucchini pie(the pie that does the impossible by making its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Using a 10-inch pie plate, sprinkle zucchini, tomatoes, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand).
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice in bowl.
Mix flour, garlic powder and paprika in shallow dish.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip in egg mixture; coat with flour mixture.
Brown on both sides in margarine in skillet.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa. Add milk, oil and vanilla. Mix only until smooth. Add nuts (if desired). Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Then mix together brown sugar and 6 tablespoons cocoa (level). Sprinkle over batter and pour boiling water over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Very good served with vanilla ice cream.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a Bundt pan well with cooking oil spray.
Put frozen bread rolls evenly around bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Add nuts.
Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with aluminum foil and let rise overnight. Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Take off foil for an additional 5 minutes.
Invert on serving plate immediately.

title: got-no-time chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour rice into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spoon 1 can of soup over rice (can be chunky).
Season.
Layer chicken on top of rice/soup.
Add 3 cans of water (to midline chicken).
Spoon second can of soup over chicken parts and coat well.
Sprinkle remaining seasoning pouch over entire contents. Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Take off foil.
Add water to 1/2 inch in rice.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes until chicken browns.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in egg until light.
Mix in flour, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in fruit, nuts and chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until firm and lightly brown around edges.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In large bowl, mix whipped topping and pudding until well blended.
Add pineapple and marshmallows and mix well.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: This
is
an
easy
skillet
dinner.
Brown pork chops. Place on each pork chop a ring of green pepper, filling center with 1 teaspoon raw rice.	Cover with a slice of onion and top with 1 slice tomato.
Add	about
cup
water.
Cover	and simmer until rice is tender.

title: chris' pork chops
directions: Wash chops and pat dry.
Place in roaster pan on rack. Sprinkle on sauce and then salt.
Rub into meat.
Bake in 375° oven approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: snow peaks
directions: In small saucepan, heat corn syrup until boiling.
With electric mixer at high speed or with eggbeater, beat egg whites until they form soft peaks when beater is raised.
Add salt slowly. Pour in syrup continuing to beat until frosting is fluffy and forms peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
This is a frosting for any cake.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil together chicken, celery and onion.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer chopped chicken, boiled eggs, the chopped onion and celery.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In a saucepan, melt butter. Add flour and buttermilk.
Stir until blended well.
Pour this evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: pam's rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water and yeast.
Mix 1 cup sugar, instant potatoes and 1 cup warm water together.
Add first mixture to second mixture, then add 1/2 cup oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add to yeast mixture.
Work together.
Pour 4 to 5 Tbsp. oil into big bowl.
Pour dough into bowl; form into ball coated with the oil. Cover with towel overnight.
The next morning, punch down dough. Knead on flour surface; cut out rolls and put on greased baking sheet (spray sheet with Pam cooking spray).
Put oil on top of rolls.
Allow to rise at least 4 hours.
Cover with paper towel or regular towel while rising.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 40 rolls.

title: quick sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan and break one loaf of bread into walnut size pieces into bottom of pan.
Mix pudding, butter and sugar together in a bowl.
If it is too thick, add 1/2 tablespoon of milk.
Pour 1/2 of this over dough in pan.
Break remaining loaf over sugar mixture and pour rest of sugar over top of all. Sprinkle nuts and raisins after each layer of sugar mixture.
Let rise to top of pan at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; turn upside down on plate.

title: special carrots
directions: Put in saucepan and cook until tender.

title: my best pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Fork stir or use wire whisk to stir flour before measuring.
Cream oleos, butter and shortening with sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add eggs two at a time with 1 cup flour and beat well.
Add flavorings and beat until batter is creamy and fluffy.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients
in order given.
Bake in a greased dish or pan, 12 x 9 x 2-inch, at 325° for 1 hour.
Leave in dish.

title: grandma's butterscotch pie
directions: Stir brown sugar and margarine in heavy skillet over medium heat until sugar begins to caramelize, stirring constantly.
Mix flour, cornstarch, egg yolks and a small amount of milk in a bowl. Stir in remaining milk gradually.
Very slowly stir into carmelized mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Add sugar slowly, beating constantly, until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie.
Seal to edge of crust.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly browned.

title: west african avocado-pineapple spread
directions: Cut avocados; scoop out flesh and mash.
Add lemon juice and mix.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Saute the sausages with the garlic and round onion.
Pour in the red kidney beans and their liquid.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer until flavors are well integrated.
Serve on hot rice with Louisiana hot sauce to spice it up to suit individual taste. Tabasco may also be used.
Also, serve with coleslaw.

title: christmas casserole cookies
directions: Add the sugar to the beaten eggs. Beat until fluffy. Stir in the coconut, vanilla, dates, nuts and almond extract.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and stir well with wooden spoon.
Cool.
Roll into balls and cover with granulated sugar.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook mushrooms, onion and garlic about 5 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in vegetables and basil.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, toss together vegetable mixture.
Cook macaroni, olives, soup and vinegar.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours.
Just before serving, add cheese.
Toss lightly.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in bacon drippings.
Combine eggs, buttermilk, and soda, mix well.
Stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each frankfurter into 10 pieces.
Dip each piece into the batter covering completely (wooden picks work well for dipping).
Drop into 3 or 4-inch deep hot oil and cook until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Insert party pick and serve immediately with mustard, catsup or picante sauce. Makes about 10 servings.
To make corn dogs leave frankfurters whole and insert wooden skewers.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kofta kabobs
directions: Mix lamb and seasonings.
Shape into tiny, oval shaped nuggets and thread on cocktail toothpicks (2 nuggets on each one).
Broil or barbecue for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves.

title: taco dip
directions: Fry meat and drain fat.
Add dry taco mix and water.
Simmer approximately 5 minutes (until water evaporates).
Add beans and stir with meat.
Layer alternating mixture and cheese in microwave bowl.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve with regular tortilla chips or taco chips.
Can be reheated in oven until bubbly or can do in crock-pot.

title: caribbean chicken with rice
directions: Simmer the chicken in two tablespoons of water in a large skillet for 40 minutes.
Add green pepper and onion slices. Continue to simmer until thicken is done.
Pour apricot pineapple preserves on chicken, green pepper and onion.
Stir gently.
Place pineapple rings on chicken and vegetables.
Spoon preserves onto the pineapple rings.
Simmer five more minutes.
Serve over favorite flavor of rice.
Serves six.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble corn bread and white bread and mix with crackers. Saute vegetables in butter.
Add to bread mixture and mix well. Add enough broth to moisten well.
Add eggs, salt and pepper along with chestnuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 1 hour or until firm.
Top with giblet gravy.

title: frozen angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to milk.
Add milk to dry mixture; mix well.
Turn onto floured surface; fold over, working in small amounts of flour several times.
Pat or roll out to desired thickness; cut and place on greased cookie sheet and freeze.
As soon as the biscuits are frozen, place in freezer bags or containers.
To use, defrost 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 400° until brown.
This recipe makes 60 to 80 small biscuits or about 35 medium biscuits.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fruit of your choice can be pineapple, peaches, strawberries, pears, grapes, bing cherries, or fruit cocktail.

title: english pea salad
directions: Let stand overnight or at least a couple of hours.
Add a dash of Accent (optional).
After setting overnight, if is seems dry, add a little mayonnaise.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Combine rice and corn; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
Cover with the onion and green pepper.
Add ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over second can of tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
Cover with 4 strips of bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Take cover off a while to get brown, about 1/2 hour.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put stew beef into crock-pot; cover with water.
Cook overnight.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Make cream sauce with butter, flour, salt and half and half. Then add Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, Tabasco and black pepper to cream sauce mixture.

title: adobo
directions: Brown meat in garlic and onion until the moisture disappears. Pour in mixture of vinegar, shoyu, sugar and spices.
Simmer about 10 minutes before turning meat.
Turn meat and cook on slow heat for a couple hours.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Brown sausage well; drain.
Put in bowl; add garlic powder, parsley, basil and Parmesan cheese.
Cool, then add beaten eggs; mix well.
Open crescent rolls and separate each into 2 halves. Lay flat but don't roll out dough.
Press seams together to make rectangle.
Fill with meat mixture, then sprinkle with cheese. Roll up lengthwise.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 rolls.

title: buttercream cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll in pecan size ball.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Can either flatten out with glass dipped in flour or leave round.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: hot cakes or pancakes
directions: Beat egg, milk and fat.
Then add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Place 1 tablespoon salt on griddle (or iron skillet) and rub with a paper towel.
Shake off the salt.
When your hot cakes are covered with bubbles, turn.
Serve with melted butter and equal parts of honey and orange juice, or just plain syrup.

title: easy stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts until 1/4-inch thick.
Put stuffing in middle; fold in half.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Heat up chicken gravy to serve over breasts.
Enjoy.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry glaze for pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and Karo; cook until thick. Add red jello.
Cool.
Stir in strawberries.
Put in a baked pie shell.

title: easy chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and butter until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Line bottom of baking dish with 1/2 cracker/wafer crumbs.
Spread egg mixture evenly over crumbs. Spread pineapple evenly over egg mixture.
Top with whipped cream and another layer of crumbs.
Set in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: chuck wagon crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain. Stir in soup, enchilada sauce and seasonings; simmer while preparing crust.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Brown roast after seasoning real good with salt and pepper. Put roast in crock-pot and add remaining ingredients. Let cook 8 to 10 hours. Cooks while you're at work.

title: stove-top baked beans
directions: Cook
bacon
until crisp;
drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in
drippings
until
tender.
Add
beans and crumbled bacon with rest of ingredients.
Simmer in nonstick pan for 30 to 45 minutes. Time of preparation: 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grate potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix soup, cheese, onion and sour cream and pour over potatoes.
Spread corn flakes over top and drizzle with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Sift sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add chopped nuts.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter.
Mix well.
Bake in 8-inch pie plate for 40 minutes at 325°.
Cut as pie; serve with ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6.
Freezes well.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread rolls on a cookie sheet or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as instructed.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cooled roll crust.
Cover with vegetables of your choice, such as onions, carrots, cauliflower, cheese, broccoli, radishes, mushrooms, peppers, etc.
Cut and enjoy.

title: flavorful herb bread
directions: Heat milk, fat, sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in a large mixing bowl; stir until dissolved. Add milk mixture, egg, chives, parsley and oregano.
Stir in 2 cups flour, beating until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn dough onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease dough completely.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Lightly spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put a few cherries, cut in half, in bottom of pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer in pan with raisins and nuts.
Boil brown sugar and margarine until sugar dissolves.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
A very simple coffeecake, pretty to look at and easy to make.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix thoroughly into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and bake 3 hours, without peeking, in 300° oven.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.
Can also be made in crock-pot.
Cook 8 hours over low heat.

title: theo's watergate salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with pudding mix by pouring into pineapple.
Stir and add rest of ingredients by hand.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together well.
Add water and margarine.
Cook on medium heat for about 3 minutes or until it thickens.

title: orange cake
directions: In a bowl, mix together 1/2 cup sugar and juice from orange. Set aside.
Reserve orange rind.
In second bowl, cream together 1 cup sugar, salt and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir. Add sour milk (or 1 tablespoon vinegar in sweet milk).
Sift in flour and baking soda.
Grind together orange rind and raisins.
Mix into batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Punch many holes with a toothpick all over the top of the cake. Spoon sugar and juice mixture over top. Serve with whipped topping or as is.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk mixture and vanilla.
Blend.
Add flour and cocoa mixture and blend.
Add hot water and blend.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes in greased and floured pan (13 x 9-inch).
Frost with Caramel Icing (recipe follows).

title: pineapple party salad
directions: Drain syrup from crushed pineapple.
To the syrup, add water to make 2 cups.
Heat liquid.
Add both packages of gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly oiled mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: chicken and spinach divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2 to 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Arrange spinach in dish; top with chicken.
In medium bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; blend well. Spoon over the chicken.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs (or croutons).
Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven for 30 to 45 minutes, until hot.
Serves 4.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix until well blended.
Delicious with sliced apples, chunk pineapple, strawberries, cantaloupe, watermelon, peaches and kiwi.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to creamed mixture. Place flour in large bowl, add dates, orange slices and nuts.
Stir in to coat each piece.
Add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
Mix by hand.
Put in greased, floured 13 x 9-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: casserole italiano
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; set aside. Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet over medium heat.
Remove excess grease.
Add salt, oregano, soup, water and cooked macaroni.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish; garnish with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: On low heat, melt
cream
cheese
and cream of mushroom soup. Stir and do
not
burn.
When
melted, remove from heat and add remaining
ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight to
incorporate the flavors.
Serve with crackers or vegetables of your choice.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° according to the package directions.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in it with a knife or fork. Pour condensed milk and pina colada mixture over cake. Cool for 2 hours.
Spread Cool Whip and top with coconut. Keep refrigerated.
