title: fettuccine
directions: Grate Romano and Parmesan cheese and set aside.
Prepare 1 pound of fettuccine according to package directions.
Melt butter in small saucepan.	Add mushrooms, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic powder.
Saut five minutes.
Add whipping cream and cook 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sour cream and warm a little. Drain fettuccine and place in large pasta bowl.
Add sauce, grated Mozzarella and Romano cheeses and toss gently.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar, lemon juice and liquid artificial sweetener.
Chill. When gelatin begins to gel, add vegetables.
Pour into square pan. Place in refrigerator.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares; place on lettuce leaf.
Yield:
5 servings.
Carbohydrate 2 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 4.
One serving = free food exchange.

title: turkey delight
directions: Brown almonds and cornflakes in butter.
Pour in casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Then mix rest of ingredients and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt beaulah's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook all vegetables (onions, peppers and garlic) with tomatoes until all are well cooked.
Run through food mill.
Mix rest with vegetables.
Cook until thick, at least an hour or more.
Take out bay leaves.
Pack in hot jars.
Have lids hot.
Can process in hot water bath.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Put zucchini in saucepan with 1/2 cup water or orange juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover; cook gently until tender, enough to mash or puree (10 minutes).
Drain and mash or puree in blender. You should have about 1 cup.
Sift flour with baking soda and powder, spices, cocoa and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Beat eggs in separate bowl until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; mix thoroughly. Slowly beat in oil.
Beat to keep mixture light.
Mix zucchini and buttermilk.
Stir flour mixture into egg mixture.
Blend on low speed until well mixed.
Stir in vanilla, orange rind and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° until cake shrinks slightly from sides and toothpick comes clean when stuck in center.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil rice in 3 1/2 cups water.
Heat oil in heavy skillet. Brown onions and garlic; cut up chicken livers and add to onion-garlic mixture.
Saute until cooked and crumbly.
Add green onions, parsley, chili pepper, salt and pepper.
Add rice with cooking liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally.

title: laban-cucumber-yogurt salad
directions: First peel and dice cucumber.
Mash the garlic with salt to taste and add to yogurt, then add diced cucumber; last add spearmint leaves.
Serves 4 to 6 people.
Chill before serving.

title: hanky panky party snack
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef with fennel seed. Drain grease. Stir in rest of ingredients until Velveeta cheese melts.
Spread on rye (this can be frozen at this point).

title: banana bread
directions: Measure flour, sugar and baking powder into a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add margarine, milk and bananas.
Mix at low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit salad delight
directions: Combine instant pudding mix (dry) with fruit cocktail and pineapple with juice.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in whipped topping. Chill.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Stir in thawed coconut.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Frost cake with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle almonds over each layer. Refrigerate.
This cake freezes well.

title: deb's famous cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Place eggs, oil and milk in another bowl and beat together, then add to the dry ingredients.
Fold in the rhubarb.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon topping all over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dried cranberry scones
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Stir flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in cold butter until crumbly.
Add berries and toss. Slowly pour in half and half while mixing vigorously.

title: scampi basquaise
directions: Heat olive oil and butter (approximately 1 1/2 teaspoons each is plenty).
Add shrimp and saute briefly.
Add shallots, cognac and flambe.
Add tomatoes, peas, wine and spinach leaves and reduce heat to low for a few minutes.
Sprinkle on raspberry vinegar. Season with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Serve over saffron rice or spaghetti.

title: northern-style lasagna
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Spoon off fat.
Add beef and onion. Cook until meat is browned and is thoroughly cooked and no pink remains, stirring once to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; set aside.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: danish wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Using electric mixer, cream sugar and butter in large bowl until blended.
Add cream cheese.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well.
This is good with taco salad.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Mix together into dough all the ingredients.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
This should be quite a bit larger than the pan as it forms the top.

title: boiled and baked potatoes
directions: Wash the potatoes; put them in a large pan and cover with cold water.
Add the salt and boil for 30 minutes.
Drain and put in an oven preheated to 450°.
Bake for another 20 minutes.
They will have a frosty appearance due to the large amount of salt in the boiling water, which dries on the surface when they are baked and gives them a great flavor.

title: sausage pies
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease; set aside.
Layer bottom of pie shell with part of the cheese, part of the sausage, remaining cheese and remaining sausage.
Beat the eggs and add 3/4 cup milk. Add a little salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage, then bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Be sure to drain grease off sausage.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, peanut butter and sugars until creamy. Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, then oats, chocolate pieces and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil 1 1/2 minutes, then remove and add the oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Blend. Beat and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
The cookies will harden and no baking is necessary.

title: pumpkin yeast bread
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast and spices.
In saucepan, heat milk, butter, brown sugar and salt until warm; stir constantly. Add to dry mixture.
Stir in pumpkin and beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Dough will be moderately stiff.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (5 to 8 minutes).
Shape into ball and place into lightly greased bowl, turning once.
Cover; set in warm place and let rise until double in size (about 1 hour). Punch down; shape into loaf.

title: pinto beans(those famous beans)
directions: Double bean
depth
with
water to boil in 8 pound size large roaster.
Simmer.
Add
ham shanks, caster oil, onions, peppers, garlic
and
fresh peppers, cumin, m.s.g., sugar and salt.	Keep water
at bean level.
With all additions makes 8 plus gallons.

title: creamy cheese chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup, chicken, onion, sour cream, Ro-Tel, flour and butter in saucepan.
Heat a few minutes over medium heat until well mixed and bubbly.
Spoon 2 to 3 large spoonfuls of sauce into individual flour tortillas; add a little cheese.
Roll up and place in greased casserole dish.
Bake approximately 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cook sugar, egg yolk, vinegar, water and flour until thickened and smooth.
Before removing from heat, stir in butter and lemon extract. Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made with the 3 egg whites, salt and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Brown in moderate oven.

title: spinach squares
directions: Put butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish and melt in oven. Remove. Beat eggs well in bowl.
Blend in flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese, spinach and onion and mix well.
Spoon mixture into baking dish and level off. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove and cook for 45 minutes. Cut into bite size (about 1-inch) pieces.
Can be frozen and reheated at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large heavy pot, brown meat in drippings.
Remove and add flour and cook slightly.
Add onions, parsley, shallots and garlic.
Cook until soft.
Add water, rice, seasons and sausage. When it comes to a boil, lower heat to lowest point and cook about an hour, covered tightly.
Do not peek!!
Remove lid and let cook a few minutes more if necessary to dry rice a little.
Serves 6 to 8.
Goes well with salad and garlic bread.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Mix together milk and pie filling until mix begins to get thick.
Blend in Cool Whip, then add Jackson vanilla wafers and bananas.

title: garlic rice
directions: Cook onions, red bell pepper and garlic in saucepan until tender.
Add water, bouillon and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: harriette's pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and spices; beat well 2 1/2 minutes.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat only well enough to blend.
Bake in a well-greased loaf pan for 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix together well.
Grease pans and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: party bacon sandwiches
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Spread each slice with undiluted soup.
Place small amount of cheese in center of bread.
Roll up diagonally.
Wrap with 1 slice bacon; secure with toothpicks. Place sandwiches on broiling pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: s.o.s.
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper together. Brown.
Add 2 cans tomatoes.
Let cook on medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Add brown gravy; stir together.
Cook about 5 minutes. Serve on toast.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix and roll out dough.

title: mexican green bean and corn salad
directions: Combine beans, corn, green peppers, onion and chili peppers in medium-size bowl.
Beat together oil, vinegar, chili powder, sugar, salt and oregano.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Season with pepper.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Toss with tomato just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bananas foster
directions: Cut bananas in half lengthwise, then cut into quarters.
Simmer bananas in butter for a few minutes.
Add brandy and rum.
Ignite and let alcohol burn off.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: mexican dish
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small cubes and brown in skillet with butter.
Grease bottom of baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and cut tortilla shells in small cubes and place in bottom of pan.
Mix soup, milk, taco sauce and green chili peppers together.
Add browned chicken breasts (cubed) to mixture.
Pour over tortilla shells; sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: ranch buffalo wings
directions: Blend flour and dressing mix thoroughly in Ziploc bag.
Melt butter.
Dip wings in butter, then shake in bag to coat.
Arrange in shallow baking dish and drizzle with malt vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes to brown.

title: creamsicle cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs evenly in ungreased pan.
Press down lightly. Blend cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and liqueur until smooth.
Stir in eggs and sour cream.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 375° in 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fruit on top of whipped cream.
(Use mandarin orange slices on top.)

title: fried ice cream(serves 4)
directions: Scoop out balls of ice cream measuring about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Freeze until firm.
In a medium bowl combine corn flakes, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll frozen ice cream balls in corn flake mixture and freeze again.
Beat egg.
Dip coated balls into egg, roll again in crumbs and freeze again.
(For a thicker coating, remove from freezer, roll a third time in egg and crumbs and freeze again.)
When ready to serve, heat vegetable oil in a deep fryer to 350°.
Place one or two frozen balls on a slotted spoon and lower into hot oil.
Cook 1 minute and remove immediately.
Drizzle with honey and top with whipped cream.

title: hallelujah white cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Thoroughly cream sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add milk alternately with blended flour, 3 teaspoons of baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites with remaining 1 teaspoon baking powder until stiff but not dry.
Gently fold egg whites into first mixture.
Empty batter into prepared pans.
Bake about 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool layers on wire cake racks.
While still warm, split layers horizontally.
Spread layers with jelly and put together in stack.
Frost top and sides with Amen Frosting.

title: pennsylvania dutch shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, shortening and salt.
Take out 1 cup of mixture; set aside for topping.
Combine molasses, baking soda and water; add to dry ingredients.
Divide mixture between two 8-inch unbaked pie shells.
Top with reserved crumb topping (1/2 cup for each pie).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: london broiled roast with gravy-mustard marinade
directions: Place meat in large baking dish.
Combine all ingredients in small bowl and blend well, using wire whisk or blender.
Pour mixture over meat.
Let marinate for 30 minutes, turning several times.
Remove meat and place in broiler pan.
Broil 3 or 4 inches from heat.
Cook 7 minutes on each side for medium rare or cook until desired doneness.
Brush with remaining marinade after first turn.

title: uncle tom's shrimp dip
directions: Mince onion and garlic.
Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Spread on crackers and enjoy!

title: nut crunchies
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave.
Pour over mixture; stir until coated.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Put in a measuring cup the orange juice, melted butter and enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Add this liquid to the well beaten egg.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Mix well, then stir in the cranberries.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 1 regular size loaf. This is best if not cut for 24 hours.
It mellows with age.
Freezes well.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, roll of chili con carne, tomato juice and ketchup.
Cook 15 minutes or longer, stirring constantly .
Makes a large batch of chili.

title: christmas yule log
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients. Add and mix well all other ingredients except paprika.
Form into 2 rolls and sprinkle with paprika for wooden log effect.
Chill.
Slice thin on crackers.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Pan-boil peppers for 5 minutes; drain upside down.
Brown hamburger and onion together and add salt, pepper, tomatoes, water, uncooked long grain rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 cup sharp Cheddar cheese.
Stuff peppers and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
To freeze, let cool, them put in bags and freeze.

title: mr. lee's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed (substitute juice, drained from canned pineapple for water), add extra slice (diced fine) to cake mix.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
To this juice, add water to make 2 cups liquid.
Grind apples and cranberries.
Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in the boiling water.
Add the 2 cups of liquid.
Stir until sugar and Jell-O are dissolved.
Add pineapple and then ground apples and ground cranberries.
Refrigerate to set.
Stir several times while it is setting.

title: turkey parmesan
directions: In 12-inch skillet, heat oil with garlic over medium heat. Add turkey in single layer; sprinkle with pepper flakes.
Cook 4 minutes and turn.
Spoon pizza sauce evenly over turkey.
Top with 6 Cheese Italian Recipe Blend.
Cook over low heat about 3 minutes more or until turkey is cooked through and cheese is melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, eggs, sugars and vanilla, then add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add the milk chocolate, broken into small chunks, and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo over low heat.
Add juice and cook until thick.
Add soda, salt, pepper and milk.
Simmer until hot through (without boiling).

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine them with the rest of the ingredients except corn flake mixture.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chocolate marshmallow brownies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add 1 cup chocolate chips and vanilla. Stir until smooth. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, soda and salt. Add nuts.
Mix until blended.
Turn into a greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven. Cover top immediately with marshmallows. Cool in pan.

title: portuguese pickled pork(vinha d' alhos)
directions: Cut pork into 2-inch cubes.
Put garlic, peppers, salt and vinegar into blender and mix together for about half a minute. Pour over pork and let it marinate overnight, turning it at least a couple of times.
Cook pork in marinade until done.
(Be very careful that you don't overcook it.)
Drain. Brown in skillet until nice and brown.
If making a large amount, you can brown pork under the broiler.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Blend all ingredients, adding chicken last.
Open crescent rolls, dividing in 4 rectangles and pressing dough together where it would divide.
Spoon mixture into center of each rectangle. Bring opposite corners together and pinch, forming a nice square. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy hawaiian torte
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg, vanilla and pineapple and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients. Turn into well-greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: honey almond triangles
directions: Sift flour, allspice, ginger and cinnamon into a bowl; add butter and rub in well.
Add brown sugar, slivered almonds and egg yolks.
Mix and add enough milk to blend a stiff but pliable dough, then turn onto a floured board and knead lightly.
Divide mixture in half and roll out each half into a 12-inch square. Place one square on a large greased baking tray; spread liberally with honey and sandwich other square on top.
Beat the egg whites until light and foamy, then brush over the top and cook in a moderately hot oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a golden brown.
Leave on tray to cool, then cut into triangles.
Enjoy!

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown steak in shortening over high heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly; cook over high heat for 5 minutes. Turn off heat; let stand 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Boil potato, unpeeled, until well done.
Peel and mash.
Add vanilla and enough sugar to form a heavy dough.
Knead lightly on a floured surface sprinkled with the sugar.
Roll out on surface until about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread on peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill.
Slice and refrigerate until firm.

title: gourmet meatballs
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a bowl.
Form into balls and brown in butter in a Dutch oven.
Add rest of onions and saute.
Add broth.
Heat.
Thicken with flour and water mixture. Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: caramel nut crunch
directions: Heat
oven
to
Butter a large 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan
or use Pam.
Heat brown sugar, corn syrup, margarine
and salt
in
quart saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cereal and nuts until well coated.
Spread in
pan.
Bake 15
minutes.
Cool until slightly firm, 5 to 7 minutes;
loosen with
metal
spatula.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in covered container.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: "bailey's" irish creme
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cream, in blender.
Stir in heavy cream.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: enchiladas
directions: Gravy should be rather thin.
In another skillet, heat oil and fry tortillas (flat).
(Do not cook hard.)
Put tortillas in gravy; remove to 9 x 13-inch pan and put spoonful of ground meat mixture in tortilla.
Roll up.
When finished, put remainder of gravy over enchiladas.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rainbow cake(a cake of great promise)
directions: Take batter; pour a portion into two different cake pans.
Add food coloring (preferably two different colors).
Layer in each pan the batter and food coloring.
After layering is complete, take a knife and gently draw it through the batter.
Bake at 300° to 350°, depending on oven.

title: dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Debone chicken; save broth.
Add egg, water, oil, and salt; beat well.
Add flour slowly.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out; let stand for 20 minutes.
Strip and drop into boiling broth.
After the dumplings get done, add 1 small can of Pet milk and 1 stick of butter.

title: salmon party roll
directions: Mix all ingredients very well, then place on waxed paper in any form.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.
Garnish with parsley flakes or chopped nuts.
Serve on crackers or bread for sandwiches.

title: seafood linguine(low-fat)
directions: Cook linguine as you would.
In frying pan chop up garlic and put teaspoon of oil when garlic cooked.
Use 2 seafood bouillon for each bouillon you need 2 cups of boiling water to it so you would need four cups of boiling water.
Put water and bouillon in frying pan once bouillons dissolved.
Add your fish.
Once shrimp or whatever fish you use is done just pour it over linguine.
It tastes just like oil and garlic and very low in fat.

title: cream cheese tea biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Roll dough out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits and place on bake sheet.
On each biscuit, make an indentation and fill with cherry preserves.
Preheat oven to 400°. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry-rhubarb jam
directions: Note:
Any pie filling can be used with jello to go with it.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients in food chopper; salt and drain overnight.
Cook remaining ingredients until thick.
Add to vegetables.
Heat and seal in hot jars.

title: philly pound cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs; mix at low speed until blended.
Gradually add flour with baking powder, mix at low until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mexican steak and beans
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch pieces.
Mix flour, chili powder, salt, pepper and cumin (Optional); coat meat with flour mixture.
Heat oil in an 8 inch skillet; brown meat over medium heat.
Drain fat. Stir in water, chili sauce, celery and onion; heat to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until meat is almost tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Add carrots; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in green peppers and beans (with liquid); cover and simmer until green pepper is tender.

title: no-bake strawberry dessert(low calorie)
directions: Arrange cake cubes in a single layer in a 13-in. by 9-in. by 2-in. dish.
In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in strawberries.
Pour over cake and gently press cake down. Refrigerate until set.
About 1 hour.
In a bowl, whisk milk and pudding for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Spoon over jello layer.
Spread with whipped topping.
Refrigerate until serving.
(We also thought it would be good if you used strawberry/banana jello and put bananas in with the pudding layer.) It looks nice in a glass dish, yields 20 servings.
NUTRITIONAL ANALYSIS:
1 serving= 92 calories, 2 g. fat, 2 mg cholesterol. 172 mg. sodium, 16 g carbs, 1 g fiber, 2 g protein.
Diabetic Exchange: 1 starch.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand several hours before serving.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter; pour over sugar.
Add eggs, flour, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a shallow dish or pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Makes 20 (2-inch) squares.

title: preacher burgers
directions: Mix well, then make into patties.
Grill.

title: beef birds
directions: Sprinkle beef with flour.
Pound flat on both sides. Cut into strips wide enough to roll up.
Add enough liquid to breadcrumbs to make manageable.
Add sage, salt, onions, and celery to make stuffing.
Place stuffing in center of meat strip and roll up. Secure with skewers so stuffing stays in side.
Place oil in pan over medium high heat.
Brown birds on each side.
Make gravy with remaining liquid, adding needed water and flour.
Place birds in a baking dish.
Pour gravy over meat and bake at 350° or until tender.
Mushroom soup maybe used as gravy.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: In a large bowl, soak eggplant in salted water for at least 1 hour; drain well.
In a large skillet, saute eggplant and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Transfer to a greased 1 quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mex-italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Transfer to large bowl. Combine picante sauce, dressing, basil, cheese and cumin.
Mix well.
Add beans, peas, celery and olives.
Mix well.
Chill. Just before serving, add tomatoes and avocado.
Serve with additional grated Parmesan cheese and picante sauce.

title: "better than sex" cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on the box.
While still warm, punch holes with handle of wooden spoon in cake.
Mix pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes, then pour over cake.
When cake is cool, spread prepared instant pudding over pineapple on cake.
Top with Cool Whip; spread evenly over cake. Garnish with coconut, nuts and cherries.

title: honey coffee cake(low-fat)
directions: Combine baking mix, honey, oil, egg whites and milk.
Beat 30 seconds.
Spread batter into an 8-inch pan spread with Pam. Sprinkle with cinnamon and drizzle with honey.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serves 4 with 160 calories and 3.2 g fat.

title: pork chops and scalloped potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Place in casserole in layers. Sprinkle flour, chopped onion and salt between layers.
Fill casserole within 1 1/2-inches from top.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes and add milk.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 or 2 hours at 350°.

title: caramel layer choc-squares
directions: In double boiler, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; cook over hot water, stirring constantly until caramels are melted.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Mix by hand until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes, then spread melted caramels over crust, then crumble the rest of the dough over top and bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool; may require refrigeration about 30 minutes, then cut into squares.
May eat it warm; squares may crumble.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and oleo.
Cook until sugar dissolves. Add cornstarch that has been blended with cold water.
Cook slowly until clear, 8 minutes.
Add lemon juice and grated peel.
Cook 2 minutes.
Slowly add the egg yolks beaten with the 2 tablespoons of milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Fold the egg whites into filling.
Pour into pie shell and top with meringue.

title: mom's sugar cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in unbaked pie shell with fingers, gently. Mix milk and half and half.
Pour in shell.
Mix gently with fingers.
Dot butter on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour until mixture is quivery.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Mix butter, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs.
Alternate flour and ginger ale.
Mix well.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: iced tea
directions: In a pitcher, steep 4 tea bags in 1 cup of boiling water for 30 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup of sugar while water is still hot. Squeeze the juice from 1 lemon and add to tea.
Squeeze 1 orange and add to tea.
After 30 minutes, add 3 cups cold water.
Pour in glasses over ice.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk; heat thoroughly.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: hamantashen
directions: Cream the soy margarine with the back of a wooden spoon and gradually add sugar.
Beat the mixture until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to mixture.
Stir to make a soft dough.
Chill in the refrigerator for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar in casserole dish.
Beat in eggs.
Add pineapple and bread.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandma's corn pudding
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs and milk. Add sugar and corn, mixing well. Cut bread in 1/2-inch cubes and place into a greased 9-inch square baking dish. Pour egg-corn-milk mixture over the bread. Dot with butter. Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes
out clean.

title: lace cookies
directions: Dissolve sugar in butter and let cool.
Add dry ingredients, then egg and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until light brown.

title: oven fried rice
directions: Baked in 2-1/2 qt. casserole dish at 375° for one hour.

title: stir-fried orange beef or chicken
directions: With paring knife or zester, remove peel from oranges in thin strips; set aside.
Section peeled oranges; set aside.
With sharp knife, cut steak into 2-inch wide strips or chicken into 2-inch squares.
In shallow dish, combine meat, 2 tablespoons orange juice, soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Stir to combine; set aside.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together just before serving.
Makes a large container. Put ingredients into separate containers to be mixed before serving.

title: eliza's baked rice pudding
directions: Stir together rice and water in saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 14 minutes without removing cover or stirring.
All water should be absorbed. Heat oven to 350°.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar, the cornstarch and salt. Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add yolks and milk to sugar-cornstarch mixture; beat with rotary beater.
Stir in rice, lemon juice and raisins.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in pan of very hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally or until pudding is creamy and most of liquid is absorbed.
Remove casserole from oven but not from pan of hot water.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 6 tablespoons juice. Combine sugar and flour in a bowl. Stir in reserved juice. Add cheese and pineapple chunks. Mix well. Spoon into greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Mix melted margarine and cornflakes. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-sour cream casserole
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs; blend well.
Spoon half the crumbs into a shallow 2-quart casserole dish and cover with chicken.
Combine sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper; blend well.
Pour over chicken and top with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: persimmon punch("sujong gwa")
directions: Scrape the ginger and slice it thinly.
Add the water and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove the ginger and add the sugar to the liquid; boil for 5 minutes and cool.
Carefully remove the seeds from the persimmons and replace them with pine nuts.
Add the persimmons to the syrup and allow it to stand for 5 hours. Chill the punch and serve it in a bowl with pine nuts and cinnamon sprinkled on top.

title: mom's fried potatoes with eggs(patata fritta con uova di momma)
directions: A great lunch dish.

title: chocolate zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
(To sour 1/2 cup milk, add 1 teaspoon vinegar and let stand 10 minutes.)
Put in a deep dish cookie sheet.
Add chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 25 to 40.

title: rhubarb jam with jello
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together about 20 minutes or until thick.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in jars and seal.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain off water.
Add cheese and mushroom soup.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salsa and cream cheese dip
directions: Place block of cream cheese on plate and pour salsa to cover the block evenly.
Serve with chips and enjoy.

title: three layer lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/3 cups of sugar, flour and salt in saucepan. Gradually add water and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Stir mixture back into hot mixture.
Cook, stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring, lemon rind and butter.

title: fragrant basil biscuits
directions: Hold aside 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Blend remaining dry ingredients together.
Hold aside 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cut remaining 7 tablespoons of butter into dry mixture to form coarse crumbs.
Stir in basil.
Add yogurt, until dough clings together in lumps.
Form a ball with your hands; knead on a board until dough holds together.
Roll dough into a log form; slice to make 7 equal pieces.
Place one piece of dough in the center of a buttered 8-inch round cake pan.
Surround center piece with remaining pieces evenly.
Brush with reserved butter; sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: southwest hot chip dip
directions: Cook beef and drain well.
Mix all ingredients in crock pot. Let simmer until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips.

title: conquezo dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain well.
Then add next 5 ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Put into fondue dish and keep warm.
Serve with corn chips or favorite crackers.

title: heart-healthy beef barley vegetable soup
directions: *If on a low-sodium diet, cut down or eliminate bouillon cubes.

title: mama lech's cranberry salad
directions: Mix ground cranberries, celery, oranges and sugar.
Let stand for awhile.
Mix warm water, jello and gelatine.
Add together and refrigerate.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cold tuna salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain.
Mix in all ingredients. Put in a storage bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; butter bottom and sides of pan. Place bread cubes on bottom.
Top with cheese.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spread over cheese.
Mix eggs, cream and mustard together and pour over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk and sugar together.
Put margarine or butter in a frypan.
Dip bread into mixture and fry in pan until golden brown.
Makes 4 pieces of French toast.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Put the meat and vegetables in roaster in layers and sprinkle with seasonings.
Add tomato soup to this (rinse can with little water).
Cook 5 hours in 250 oven, covered.
Do not raise lid while cooking. This makes own gravy.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Drain cucumbers and squeeze juice. Reserve juice. Beat cream cheese with a small amount of cucumber juice until it is smooth. Add garlic powder, green pepper and dressing.
Stir in cucumbers and chill. Serve on wheat crackers.

title: chicken and ham rolls(ala suisse)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan with foil. Using a mallet flatten chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Place a piece of ham on each piece of chicken; roll up from short end. Secure with toothpick if necessary.
Combine egg, 1 tablespoon mustard and 2 tablespoons water; mix well.
Mix together Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and bread crumbs. Dip rolls in egg mixture, then in crumb mixture.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Cook broccoli until tender-crisp. Brown ground beef or sausage.
Mix all 3 and pour into greased baking dish.
Top with soup and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with package of dry cheese mixture the last 15 minutes.

title: dilly potatoes
directions: Scrape small new potatoes; cook in boiling salted water until done; drain.
Combine 1 cup sour cream, dill seed and salt; pour over potatoes.
Heat 1 to 2 minutes, turning potatoes to coat. Makes 4 servings.

title: cube steak casserole
directions: Brown cube steak and cut into bite size pieces.
Place steak in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Cut butter and place over steak.
Pour rice over this.
Pour soup mix and dissolved bouillon over rice, then add water.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. (Do not batter cube steak).

title: fruity ravioli fondue
directions: Combine mini ravioli, fruit cocktail, 2 tablespoons fruit syrup, chili sauce, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce in a fondue pot or saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Serves six.

title: oyster soup
directions: Lightly rinse and drain oysters.
Boil milk.
Wash and finely chop parsley.
Chop onions.
Saute onions and parsley in butter. When onions and parsley are soft, add oysters and cook until they curl around the edges and are hot throughout.
Add to boiled milk. Pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: bundt pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, along with buttermilk.
Add extract.
Gently fold in coconut.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes, until done.
Loosen cake from sides of pan, but do not remove.
Prepare topping and pour over cake.

title: microwave bacon wrapped mini meat loaves
directions: Combine green peppers and onion in a small bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until they are tender-crisp.
Set aside.
Layer 3 paper towels on a plate.
Arrange bacon slices on the paper towels and cover with another paper towel.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or just until bacon begins to brown.
Set aside.

title: easy fried rice
directions: Saute
vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together with 4 1/2 cups
of
hot
water.
Bake
in a covered dish at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: string bean casserole(5 people)
directions: Boil string beans and put in casserole dish.
Mix can of soup with 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix soup and milk well and mix with string beans.
Mix 1/2 can of onion rings with casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put remaining 1/2 can of onion rings on top of casserole; brown for 15 minutes.

title: beef vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight for best results.

title: mom's regal chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; salt to taste.
Fold whipped cream into mayonnaise.
Toss with chicken mixture and chill. Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat half of nectar to boiling.
Dissolve jello in nectar. Add rest of nectar.
Chill until partially set.
Add drained pineapple.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan alternating with banana slices.
Chill until firm.
Mix miniature marshmallows, cream cheese and milk.
Let set in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours.
Add Cool Whip to marshmallow and cream cheese mixture.
Put on top of jello.
Chill.

title: old fashioned caramels
directions: Boil all together, except nuts and 1 cup cream, over low heat, for 30 minutes.
Add 2nd cup of cream and boil to firm ball stage (248°).
Add nuts and pour, without stirring, into well-buttered pan.
When cold, cut into 1-inch squares.

title: three flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time), sift flour and baking powder together.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Add flavorings.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan.
Do not open oven door during first hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut into shapes. Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar.

title: dutch pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight to let flavor go through.
Serve cold on lettuce.

title: old english pie
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar; beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Add nuts and apples.
Mix and pour into a well-greased pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: jane anne's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together; put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add topping.

title: cho-pie
directions: Pour in baked pie shell.

title: seafood fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add garlic and onion; saute until onion is tender.
Add shrimp and scallops; saute about 5 minutes. Season with parsley, basil, salt and red pepper.
Place hot fettucine in a serving dish.
Add seafood.
Toss gently to mix. Serve immediately.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Pour half of the batter into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: beef tips and noodles
directions: Note:
Can also add a small amount of McCormick Grill Mates Montreal steak seasoning.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Add 1 bottle dressing to sliced mushrooms and leave overnight. Next day, slice all other ingredients in thin slices.
Add ingredients to mushrooms.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese together until well blended.
Mix in Cool Whip. Beat until smooth. Pour in crust. Top with cherries. Refrigerate.

title: beychok's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In saucepan, melt chocolate and butter together.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and vanilla, then stir in each egg separately.
Add flour and salt.
Stir together thoroughly.
Add chopped pecans.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan and bake 50 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and cut into squares.

title: one dish casserole
directions: Place in baking dish a layer of ground beef, a layer of celery and a layer of sliced onions.
Over this pour tomato soup.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes over this.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325° until potatoes are tender.

title: cheese delights
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cream together cheese and butter; blend in flour and salt.
Form into small marble-sized balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; flatten with fork tines.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill for several hours.
Bake in 450° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen canapes.

title: caribbean carrots
directions: Place carrots in vegetable steamer; cover and steam for 2 minutes. Add sweet potatoes and steam for 8 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: buttery lemon bars
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter and the 1/2 cup powdered sugar until creamy; beat in 2 cups of the flour, blending thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly over bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: yum yum chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and brush onto clean, dry chicken pieces.
In a bowl, combine crackers and spices; crush. Dip buttered chicken into dry mixture and place into a baking pan. Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes (longer for more chicken).
Good with wild rice!

title: corned beef bread dip
directions: Mix the ingredients well and chill.
Use 1 loaf unsliced bread, preferably not white.
I like a round pumpernickel.
Remove bread from inside the loaf, leaving a 1-inch border around the outside.
Spoon dip into center of loaf and serve with small pieces of torn rolls around outside of loaf on a platter.
Good with rye rolls.

title: nevada's cole slaw
directions: Add sugar, salt and pepper to vegetables.
Do not stir.

title: quesidillas
directions: Cover tortilla with shredded cheese.
Cook on High for 1 minute or until cheese melts in microwave.
Dress it up with taco sauce, jalapenos or shredded chicken.
I like mine plain.

title: souper supper
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a large saucepan. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, 10 to 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Put lemon juice in Eagle Brand.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into two cold crusts or graham cracker crusts.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with beater. Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350°. Take out of stove when a bit shaky.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add chopped apples, nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Grease and flour 12 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together flour and soda; set aside.
Combine margarine, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mix.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 9 1/2 minutes or until brown.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: homemade churned ice cream
directions: Recipe requires a hand turn or electric churn (4-quart) ice cream freezer.

title: vegetable noodle casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine soups, milk, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic, parsley, pepper and salt: mix well.
Add noodles and vegetables: mix well.
Pour into a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Sprinkle with the remaining Parmesan.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes or until heated through.
Yield 12-14 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in large pot with onion, pepper, celery stalk, salt and pepper until meat is done and veggies begin to tenderize.
Add remaining ingredients, including chopped celery leaves and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: onion bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and sugar; let rest 5 minutes.
Add shortening, salt and 1 cup flour.
Let rest again for 5 minutes. Then add rest of flour.
Knead about 10 minutes.
Let rise until double.
Grease jelly roll pan (not oil).
Roll out; stretch dough into pan.
Poke holes; brush dough with oil.
Spread onion around. Salt and pepper lightly.
Rosemary leaves are optional.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into 3 x 3-inch squares.

title: better than mom's chicken soup
directions: In a large pot bring water to a boil. Place cut up chicken wings in the pot. When wings are almost done pour off water and replace with 4 to 5 quarts of water.
Add corn that has been cut in half, then potatoes, carrots, celery, salt and pepper, onions, scallions and bouillon cubes.
Cover and let cook on a medium flame.
When potatoes and veggies are tender, add noodles and cook for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Now it's ready to eat.
You can freeze this up to 6 months and it still tastes great!!

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together flour, butter and cream cheese.
Crumble like pie crust.
Form in walnut-size balls.
Line small pastry cups, using fingers, with dough.

title: low-fat whole wheat bread
directions: *Apple juice may be substituted instead of sugar and water.

title: chilled tomato soup with basil sorbet
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add the onion, leek and carrots.
Cook over medium heat 8 minutes, until soft and clear, but not browned.
Add chopped tomatoes, orange rind, Tabasco, salt, pepper, water and chicken stock.
Make a bouquet by tying herbs in a square of cheesecloth.
Put this in, too.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over a low flame.
Discard the bouquet garni and set tomato mixture aside to cool.
When cool, puree in blender or food processor.
Add the heavy cream.
Chill.

title: fresh country peas
directions: In
quart microwavable casserole, combine peas, onion and
water.
Cover;
vent
and
microwave on High 6 to 9 1/2 minutes,
or just until vegetables are tender; set aside. In microwavable
bowl,
microwave
bacon
until crisp; drain. Discard fat if using margarine.
Otherwise, leave 1 tablespoon fat in bowl;
stir
flour	and
sugar
into margarine or fat. Stir in broth
until
smooth.
Microwave sauce on High 1 to 2 minutes
or until
thick,
stirring
every 30 seconds.	Drain water from vegetables and add sauce; toss to coat.
Spoon into bowl; sprinkle with cooked bacon.	Serves 4.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer together in a large bowl (add beer last).
Stir lumps out, then put into buttered loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: apricot punch
directions: Dissolve jello in cold water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Freeze liquid solution.
When ready to serve, thaw and add ginger ale.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar, butter and flavoring.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well and bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.
Check with toothpick to make sure it is done.

title: buttered carrots and green pepper strips
directions: Cook carrots in 1 inch boiling salted water in covered 2-quart saucepan for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Add green pepper during last 2 minutes of cooking.
Drain, toss with butter and cheese.

title: my friend's egg casserole(excellent for brunch buffet)
directions: Beat eggs; mix in cottage cheese, grated cheese and seasonings.
Stir in chopped chilies.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: savory potato gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet until soft and transparent.
In a shallow baking dish, arrange sliced potatoes and onions in layers, sprinkling with garlic and seasonings in between layers for best flavor.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Press softened cream cheese into bottom of baking pan.
Top with chili and salsa.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.
Serve with your favorite dipping chips.

title: artichoke spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.

title: hocus pecos dip
directions: Place cream cheese in bowl and beat until smooth.
Add picante sauce and beat until no lumps of cream cheese remain.
Stir in onions, beef and seasonings.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: ham 'n broccoli rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 slices of ham on each slice of cheese.
Place broccoli spears on one end of each slice and roll up.
Place broccoli rolls, seam side down, in lightly greased shallow baking dish.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook rice.
Boil peppers until done.
Cook ground meat, onion and chopped bell peppers.
When done, add cooked rice, Ro-Tel tomatoes and celery soup.
In a pan, add bell peppers and stuff with stuffing.
At last, top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shortcake sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: teriyaki stir-fried chicken
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Fry cut chicken until golden brown.
Add teriyaki and garlic.
Cover and simmer on medium for 10 minutes.
Uncover and fry on medium high until juice has evaporated.
Serve.

title: maple walnut ice cream
directions: Blend
smooth
all
but bananas.
Slowly drop chunks of banana in while blender is running. Add more milk if unable to blend all bananas.
Ready to serve or freeze.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually and then oil, continuing to beat.
Add vanilla and zucchini; stir. Sift flour with dry ingredients and mix slightly and stir in.
Add in nuts and raisins.
Divide batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Blend cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on Jell-O and mix well.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: no-fail microwave divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 2 quart casserole. Cook on high 19-20 minutes.
Stirring every 5 minutes.
While syrup cooks, beat egg whites very stiff.
Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites and continue beating at high speed until thick. May require up to 12 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts to beaten mixture, drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper or foil.

title: lasagne
directions: *I sometimes use hamburger or sausage, but usually hamburger and sausage mixed.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and cherry juice.
Add eggs and extract.
Mix with spoon and fold in cherries.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into bite size pieces and layer into casserole dish or baking pan.
Dot liberally with butter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Now layer string beans on top.
(Pour juice from can around edges so as not to wash salt and pepper away from potatoes.)
Sprinkle string beans with 1 teaspoon of flour.
Layer pork chops on top and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with lid or tightly seal with foil.
Bake approximately 45 minutes or until pork chops are done and potatoes are fork-tender.
Uncover and bake about 10 minutes to brown chops, if desired.

title: low-cal cool pie
directions: Mix together crushed pineapple, its juice and the pudding mix. Fold in yogurt and then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell and chill.

title: lo-cal blueberry cottage cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatins in boiling water.
Cool.
Coat bottom of 6-cup mold with gelatin using a pastry brush or spoon.
Let set slightly.
Arrange 1/2 cup blueberries decoratively in gelatin layer.
Chill until firm.
Pour another thin layer of gelatin and let set.
Add blueberries, cottage cheese and yogurt to rest of gelatin and blend thoroughly.
Spoon mixture over gelatin layer in mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens and serve with mayonnaise thinned with cranberry juice.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Layer with vanilla wafers and bananas. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
This looks nice served with a little Cool Whip on top.
Finish off with a maraschino cherry.

title: froot loop cookies(easy)
directions: Melt chocolate in oven at 150° or low heat, 15 to 20 minutes. Mix in other ingredients and drop by spoon on wax paper.
These freeze well.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Dissolve soda in applesauce and add.
Sift salt, cinnamon and cloves with part of the flour and add to the first mixture.
Add more flour to make a fairly stiff batter.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
One cup raisins may be added to the batter.

title: herb potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; do not peel.
Cut into quarters or smaller. Put into plastic bag with soup mix and shake to coat potatoes. Place in single layer in baking dish.
Pour oil over and bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown and tender.

title: double delicious cookie bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely at room temperature.

title: crowned carrot cake
directions: Grease 12-cup Bundt or 10-inch tube pan with shortening; coat pan with nuts.

title: beef casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
In meantime, brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Cook until done, then add corn, chili beans and soup (cream of chicken soup may be substituted, either is good).
Add macaroni and cheese and cook until heated.
If it gets too dry, add soup can of milk or water.
Place in casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° until cheese melts.
Makes a big casserole.
May be divided into two.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Cover casserole dish after mixing all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until the sauce bubbles.
Reduce heat to 250° and cook for 4 hours.
Add 1 cup of Burgundy.
Bake 1 hour longer.
Men love it!

title: cheesy jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add cold water.
Then add crushed pineapple to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into oblong casserole dish.

title: baked crab spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in a casserole and bake for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar. Add flour, milk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and square of chocolate.
Beat eggs; add sugar and butter/chocolate mixture.
Put in flour and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour in a greased and floured pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: whoopi pies
directions: Add together.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fast double banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; tilt to cover bottom.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir with a fork or spoon until blended (about 2 minutes).
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until tooth pick inserted into center comes clean.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Serve directly from pan.
Store loosely covered.

title: squash casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Beat eggs in separate bowl.
Saut onion in margarine. Add squash, eggs, milk and brown sugar and salt to onions.
Mix well.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole, put 1 layer of 10 crushed crackers, 1 layer of squash mixture and 1 layer of cheese.
Repeat once; top with cracker crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black forest cake
directions: Can use white or yellow cake and substitute apples or peaches.

title: garden club veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with the buttered crackers and return to oven for 15 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Put bacon, hamburger and onion in crock pot.
Add beans.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to crock pot.
Simmer for 4 hours.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Pour milk over cornmeal.
Brown beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce, corn, chili powder, butter and olives.
Add eggs and cornmeal mixture.
Add oil and mix.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: For rice, follow directions for 2 cups.
Place chicken in a casserole dish; sprinkle onions over chicken.
Pour salsa over this mixture, then pour beans over this.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until just tender.
Drain.
Fry meat, onion and pepper until light brown.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Pour sauce over macaroni in casserole.
Stir well.
Cover with cheese.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower blend soup
directions: Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese, cubed.
Cover and turn off heat.
Add 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 cup of milk.
Do not boil.
Heat carefully to prevent curdling.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: easy mexican dinner
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Stir in noodles, tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 cup cheese, olives, mushrooms and seasoning.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granny's muscadine pie
directions: Separate muscadine hulls from pulp.
Add water to hulls to cover.
Cook hulls with 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 stick of butter until tender.
In a buttered baking dish, melt 1 stick of butter. In mixing bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Place fruit on top with juice.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Crust will rise to the top.

title: raisin and bran muffins
directions: Blend sugar and shortening together; add eggs and buttermilk. Pour boiling water over bran; add to buttermilk mixture.
Combine soda, salt and flour; stir into bran mixture.
Add raisins and mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin tins or baking cups.
Bake in preheated oven to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit jello cookies(welcome school's)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Then blend remaining dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Stamp with cookie stamp.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: jill's crock-pot chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Place chicken breasts, cream of chicken soup and water in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Shred chicken when done before removing from crock-pot.
Cook dumpling noodles according to package directions; drain.
Serve chicken over hot dumpling noodles.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor.
Process until smooth. Chill mixture.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in salt water for 30 minutes.
Drain. Add the chopped onion and tomatoes.
Mix the mayonnaise.

title: super sandwich
directions: Mix egg in a bowl.
Put slice of bread in the egg, then put in hot oil for a few minutes until golden brown.
Put in plate with honey and eat hot.

title: mint frosted brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; blend in sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and mix into chocolate mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Tear chicken into bite size pieces.
Put in crock-pot.
Add mushroom soup, Ro-tel tomatoes, Lipton onion soup, chicken broth and slightly cooked spaghetti.
Add Velveeta cheese. Cook on low in crock-pot until cheese is melted or longer.

title: bagel pizzas
directions: Place each bagel half on cookie sheet.
Spoon on pizza sauce. Layer on pepperoni, sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is brown and bagels are crisp.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Wash and cut into bite size pieces; slice pieces of margarine (pour over top of potatoes).
Pour 3 to 4 tablespoons soy sauce over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 400° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: veal cutlets al libera
directions: Pound cutlets flat on both sides.
Beat together eggs, water, seasonings, parsley and cheese.
Dip cutlets into flour, then into egg mixture and finally into bread crumbs, coating well on both sides.

title: chicken honey nut stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips and set aside.
In a small bowl, combine orange juice, honey, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger; mix well.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and pour into mold and freeze. Unmold about 20 to 25 minutes before serving and serve on lettuce leaves. This is a very good salad to serve during the Holidays.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix beef, rice, seasoning and eggs.
Shape into 14 or 15 balls.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Cook at 370° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cut into bite-size pieces and save broth.
Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Put in chicken. Pour drained vegetables over chicken.
Mix soup and broth in blender.
Pour over vegetables.
Do not stir.
Mix flour and milk and pour on top to form crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm on crackers.

title: easy no-cook taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Place in a large serving dish.
Layer on the following:
picante sauce, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, olives and cheese.
Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: veggies in cream sauce
directions: Heat fat; stir in flour.
Add milk slowly.
Stir until smooth. Cook and stir until thickened.
Add salt, pepper and vegetables. Makes 6 servings.

title: crab bisque
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat slowly in saucepan.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: citrus bagel
directions: Toast bagel.
Mix butter and orange peel; spread on bagel. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading the butter on bottom and sides of dish.
Combine Bisquick and sugar.
Mix milk and vanilla, then add to dry mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour into the buttered dish.
Do not stir.
Pour peaches and the syrup over the top.
Do not stir. Bake about 45 minutes.
Serve warm and top with vanilla ice cream.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, and syrup; then add pecan halves and cook until a hard ball forms in water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Beat until it begans to harden.
Drop by spoonfulls on wax paper.

title: cottage pudding with sauce
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, baking powder and milk.
Add flour to make cake batter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: yeast leavened flapjacks
directions: Add sugar and salt to milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add to milk.
Beat in flour, oil and eggs with a mixer.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour before using.
Bake pancakes on hot griddle as usual.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut out tomato cores.
Cut each tomato not quite all the way through into wedges.
Spoon out and reserve centers.
Invert tomato to drain.
Chill.
Chop tomato pulp fine and drain.
Mix corn, chopped tomatoes, onions, pepper, pimiento and salt. Combine olive oil, lemon juice and minced garlic for sauce to marinate vegetable mixture.
Pour over vegetables; mix well and chill thoroughly until serving time.
Spoon mixture into tomato cups.
Serve.

title: beef stew in crock-pot
directions: Layer all ingredients except peas in crock-pot and cook about 5 or 6 hours. Add frozen peas the last 30 minutes.

title: best in the west baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and drain.
Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add chopped onion.
Saute for a few minutes.
Place beans in a large casserole; add hamburger and all other ingredients.
Stir well and crumble in bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potatoes en casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large cake pan. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours uncovered.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in the large bowl of an electric mixer.
Mix until blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets about 2 1/2 inches apart.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Allow to rest on baking sheets for 5 minutes.
Remove with a thin, flexible spatula.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and cranberries.
Mix and let set until semi-firm.
Swirl in the sour cream.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescents and place in rectangular shaped pan.
Pinch seams to close.
Spread dough to fill entire pan.
Bake according to package directions.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef. Mix all ingredients and simmer in crockpot all day/night or cook on low heat for several hours on top of stove.

title: herb-marinated chuck steak
directions: Combine onion, parsley, vinegar, oil, mustard, garlic and thyme.
Place beef chuck shoulder steak in plastic bag; add onion mixture, spreading evenly over both sides.
Close bag securely; marinate in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours, turning at least once. Pour off marinade, discard.
Place steak on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 5 inches from heat source.
Broil about 16 minutes for rare and about 18 minutes for medium, turning once. Carve steak diagonally across grain into thin slices.
Garnish as desired.

title: punch
directions: Put all ingredients in punch bowl then start pouring 7-Up in until you finish filling punch bowl.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients with meat.
Layer with frozen tortillas. Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put cheese on top and melt.

title: washboards
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream.
Blend in eggs.
Add soda to milk; blend into mixture.
Add coconut and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Drop onto cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Prepare tube pan; generously grease pan with butter, then sprinkle in 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Shake pan gently until sides and bottom are well covered.

title: sunny citrus squares
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over pineapple juice.
Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Stir in sugar and orange juice. Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: easter beets(old family tradition)
directions: Boil eggs and peel.
Place in bowl, pour pickled beets over top.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator or several hours.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.
Always serve at Easter (old family tradition).

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Wash and leave skins on potatoes where possible.
Or pare thinly and remove eyes.
Cut into enough pieces to measure about 4 cups.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.
Mix remaining cheese and the bread crumbs; sprinkle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes longer or until top is brown and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: open-face beef tenderloin sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to very hot, 450°.
Rub beef with oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Roast in preheated very hot oven at 450° for about 35 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 130° for medium-rare.
Let stand 10 minutes. Cut into thin slices and serve on Italian bread slices with Dilled Mustard Sauce and/or Spicy Sauce.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, chopped jalapenos and onions.
Heat over medium heat.
Add cheese until desired thickness.
Fry corn tortillas flat.
When cool enough to handle, shred tortillas into large casserole dish.
Then add meat and sauce.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash dressing
directions: Cook squash, onion and celery in a small amount of water until tender.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, eggs and cornbread crumbs.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350-375.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda, and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugars, butter, and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 15x10x1-inch baking sheet.
Cook 20 -25 minutes.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Mix together ground beef, egg, cracker crumbs, 1 chopped onion, 1/4 cup green pepper and salt.
Shape into patties.
Arrange in baking dish.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut into 12 donuts.
Set them aside. Put the scraps in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Layer the next 4 ingredients into casserole dish.
Arrange the donuts and holes over the top.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over casserole and let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until set.
Remove and sprinkle 2 ounces cheese over the top.
Return to oven to melt the cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli and cook as directed. Cook rice as directed. Mix together and heat in 375° oven until bubbly hot.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter, beat eggs and add butter.
Add remaining ingredients, with corn bread mix last.
Pour into a greased 13x9 pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 20-25 min.
Test with toothpick.

title: chicken ole
directions: Cook chicken; let cool and tear into strips.
Mix soup, milk, salsa, onion and garlic.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch strips.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make layers:
sauce, tortillas, chicken, then cheese; repeat until ingredients are finished.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ladyfinger bars
directions: Beat egg
yolks
in
a
large
bowl at high speed of an electric
mixer
minutes
or until thick and lemon colored. Add sugar,
water
and
vanilla,
mixing
just until blended. Combine flour and baking powder.
Sift flour mixture over yolk mixture; gently fold in flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff
peaks form.
Gently fold egg whites into yolk mixture. Spread batter evenly in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan that has
been
coated with vegetable cooking spray and lined with parchment
paper. Bake
at
325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven
and
cool completely.
Cut
into
x 2 1/2-inch bars. Yields 60 ladyfingers.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Cover a pizza pan or cookie sheet with foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out the cookie dough into the shape of a round pizza. Bake in oven until done.
Remove from oven and sprinkle top of pizza cookie with chocolate chips, nuts, marshmallows and drizzle topping over all.
Return to oven and broil (400°) until toppings melt (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove and allow to cool before cutting into wedges to serve.

title: heavenly delight cake
directions: Bake cake as per directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While still hot, poke holes in top and pour milk and caramel topping over top. When cool, spread whipped topping on top and sprinkle crushed candy bars on top of the best cake ever!

title: italian hors d'oeuvre salad
directions: Fry sausage pieces slowly until cooked through.
Drain well on paper towels and place in large stainless steel pot or bowl that can be set on a warm stove burner.
Saute mushrooms in butter over high head, turning constantly to sear all sides.
Drain and add sausage.
Add artichoke hearts plus oil from one jar, olives, cauliflowerets.
Add generous amounts of seasonings to taste.
Mix well.
Keep pan warm during serving time, stirring occasionally or at room temperature.
Serve with cocktail picks.
If you plan to prepare this ahead of time, store cauliflowerets in plastic bag until serving time.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in vanilla, flour and nuts. Chill.
Shape dough into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on an
ungreased baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
When cold, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana muffins
directions: Spray 12 (2 1/2 inch) muffin cups with Mazola no stick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In large bowl, using fork or wire whisk, beat egg whites lightly.
Stir in mashed bananas, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture, stir until well blended.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 22 to 25 minutes or until firm to touch.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then remove and cool on wire rack.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place in hot jars. Bring liquids and salt to boil and pour over pickles in jars. Seal.

title: grape sherbet
directions: Dissolve the sugar in rich grape juice
and milk.
Mix thoroughly and freeze.

title: banana coffee bread
directions: Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in bananas.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
May take a little longer so be sure to check it.

title: macaroni pizza
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box. Drain. Beat together egg, milk, 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese and salt. Blend in macaroni and spread in greased 9 x 15-inch baking dish. Pour spaghetti sauce over macaroni. Add small bits of raw ground beef. Sprinkle on green peppers, onion, mushrooms and remaining Parmesan cheese. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: charlie's chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in pan.
Flatten out lumps in cocoa.
Add enough hot water to dissolve.
Add butter and canned milk.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour over hot buttered biscuits.

title: italian beef stew with rosemary
directions: In a large heavy skillet, brown beef in hot oil.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion, celery, garlic and carrots to pan drippings; saute until tender.
Return beef to pan.
Add tomatoes, parsley, wine, rosemary, salt and pepper; bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes the last 45 minutes of cooking.
Add peas the last 10 to 15 minutes of cooking time.
