Serve with French bread and a hearty red wine.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherries across the bottom of 9 x 13 glass baking dish, followed with pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over fruits. Cut margarine in slices and spread across the top of the mixture. Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake in 350° (preheated) oven for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: frozen lemon delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter and press into bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan and 8 x 8 inch pan.
Beat egg yolks, add milk and stir.
Add lemonade mix and beat until thick with a spoon.
Fold in whipped cream.
Mix thoroughly and pour over crust.
Beat egg whites until thick.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Spoon onto lemon mixture and spread carefully.
Brown slightly under the broiler until just golden brown.
Watch carefully it only takes a few seconds.
Then put in the freezer.
Serves 20.
You may add some yellow food coloring to lemon mixture to make it look more lemony.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Simmer in pan for 3 minutes the tomato sauce, 1/4 cup oil and 1 onion.
Add water, oregano, vinegar, chili powder, sugar and salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: In a small bowl, combine oil, vinegar, salt and black pepper. Mix all vegetables and cheese in a salad bowl.
Pour dressing over, tossing to mix well.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers very thin (do not peel).
Mix cucumbers, salt and onions and let set for 2 hours.
Drain and squeeze pickles.

title: hurry-up meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Shape into 6 (or more) loaves.
Place loaves on rack of greased broiler pan.
Spoon barbecue sauce over loaves.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, butter, orange peel and vanilla. Beat until
smooth.
Add
potatoes,
milk,
orange
juice
and coconut; mixing well.
Bake	in greased baking dish at 350° or until done (about 1 hour).

title: ozark chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, rice, lemon juice, celery, onion, mayonnaise, eggs, soup, salt and pepper thoroughly and place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix butter and stuffing mix together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except salad oil.
When blended add oil. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Spread chili on top of cream cheese and sprinkle Cheddar cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Marinate for 4 hours, then add cooked spaghetti.

title: cheese ball or cheese dip
directions: Shape into a ball or put into a small bowl.
Will keep for a long period of time in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls.
Cook over medium heat until brown, about 20 minutes.
Drain well.

title: hearty beef 'n potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks; drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can of Durkee French fried onions and tomatoes in potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; pour over beef mixture. Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix cocoa, oil and butter in saucepan over low heat until butter is melted. Add sugar and mix. Remove from heat and add eggs. Beat well (all in saucepan). Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: golden corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in greased casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: cafe brulot
directions: Allow all ingredients (except coffee) to muddle 1 hour before serving.
Blaze for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add coffee slowly.
May top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: alphabet vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine garden vegetable mix, vegetable juice cocktail, seasoned pepper and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add alphabet macaroni and potatoes.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, for about 12 to 15 minutes, until macaroni and potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla, apples, raisins and walnuts.
Add flour gradually to mixture and stir well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Make smooth cream sauce with 1 1/2 tablespoons melted margarine, flour, heavy cream and milk.
Season with pepper and paprika to taste.
Add grated and sharp cheese.
Saute onion in margarine and olive oil until soft.
Add sweet basil, marjoram, tarragon and parsley to taste.
Add cut up canned tomatoes.
Stir both types of crabmeat into cream sauce.
Add sauteed onion, tomatoes and seasonings.
Top with bread crumbs.
(I sprinkle paprika and pepper into bread crumbs.)
Bake uncovered in casserole for 25 minutes at 325°.
This is easy to do ahead and bake later.
It will serve 4 people.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix jell-o with 1 cup of boiling water per box. Mix well until dissolved. Let cool until lukewarm. Add pie filling, pineapple, and pecans. Mix together and place in dish. Refrigerate until congealed. (Blueberry pie filling and blackberry jell-o can be substitute for cherry).

title: taco soup i
directions: Cook hamburger with chopped onion.
Rinse meat and return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sausage and cheese quiche
directions: Fry sausage; drain.
Mix flour with sausage and place in bottom of pie crust.
Beat eggs, milk, cheese, salt and pepper together and pour over sausage.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry the hamburger.
Crush chips into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Put meat over chips.
Mix soup and water in frying pan together and pour over meat and chips.
Slice cheese and lay over complete top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: butternut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and flour, then add nuts. Roll in balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, bacon, onion and shredded Cheddar cheese in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar until blended. Pour mixture over broccoli mixture and toss thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fajita chicken fingers
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Spray skillet with Pam cooking spray or heat 3 tablespoons cooking oil in skillet on medium heat.
Sprinkle chicken strips heavily with fajita seasoning and fry in the skillet until lightly browned. Place onion on top of chicken fingers and put a lid on the skillet.
When onion is tender (not soft), remove lid and turn over chicken fingers.
Place tomatoes on top.
Replace the lid on the skillet until tomatoes are slightly soft.
The fajita seasoning sometimes makes the chicken appear blackened.
This is okay.
Place rice on plates and put chicken, onion and tomatoes on top.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Thaw potatoes before mixing ingredients. Mix first 8 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix the 1/4 cup melted butter with corn flakes and put on top. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Ways and 1/2 the margarine in a saucepan.
Cream rest of margarine with the sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to the margarine and sugar.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add milk, nuts and vanilla.
Stir in Milky Way mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli as to package directions.
Mix cheese with rice.
Add soup and broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream and cheese baked potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add egg and stir well. Add molasses, stirring until well mixed.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt. Beat until smooth.
The batter is soft but makes a fine cake.
Bake in shallow
greased pan. Bake for 35 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: spicy hot dog relish
directions: Dice onions in 5-quart saucepan.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 3 hours on low heat.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large pan, boil chicken broth, onion peppers, celery and mushrooms. Add Rotel and noodles, cook for 20 minutes. In baking dish add chicken, spaghetti noodle mixture and cut up velveeta cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Make instant pudding according to directions.
Add the condensed milk and mix well.
Pinch the angel food cake into pieces.
In a bowl, place a layer of cake, then pudding mixture, then Cool Whip and lastly crushed Butterfingers.
Continue until all is used, ending with Butterfingers.
Refrigerate.

title: jumbo cereal muffins
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, milk, egg and oil.
Mix in flours, baking powder and salt until flour is moistened.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Pour in paper covered tins. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 jumbo or 12 regular muffins.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl; beat eggs lightly in a smaller bowl.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and add eggs, milk and butter.	(Add extra milk to the desired consistency.)
Cook over medium heat on a nonstick griddle until bubbles surface; flip and cook until golden brown.

title: hanky pank
directions: Brown and drain beef and sausage.
Put in crock-pot.
Melt desired amount of Velveeta cheese (1/2 to 3/4 box) on top of the meat in the crock-pot.
When cheese is melted, it is ready.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Mix water and lime.

Pour over cucumbers and soak 24 hours, stirring occasionally. Rinse thoroughly and put fresh water over cucumbers; let soak 3 hours. Rinse thoroughly. Boil solution of the sugar, vinegar, salt, pickling spice, cloves and celery seed. Add cucumbers and bring to a boil again; reduce to simmer and simmer 35 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
Do not soak in aluminum or granite pan.

title: italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed on package. Rinse and drain.
Remove sausage from casing, cook with onion in skillet over low heat until browned, breaking sausage into small pieces; drain.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla. Stir until blended.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing pie with cherry pie filling or strawberries.

title: green beans with roquefort cheese
directions: Cut bacon in tiny pieces.
Cook until crisp.
Remove and saute onion in bacon drippings. Add sugar, vinegar, bean juice, salt and pepper. Pour over beans overnight. Heat; add bacon bits. Sprinkle crumbled cheese generously over beans.
May also be served at room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: barbara mandrell's tropical fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
If you use the yellow cake mix, add 1/2 cup melted margarine to the other ingredients. Pour into 9-inch Bundt pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°. Allow to cool.
Remove cake from pan and refrigerate about 1/2 hour.
Stick holes in cake with fork and spread with frosting.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl twice.
Make a hole in center and add beaten eggs and oil.
Mix together well.
Batter will be thick.
Then add carrots; mix again well.
Last, add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in floured tube pan 1 hour at 325°.
Frost with Cream Nut Frosting.

title: ruby's broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in bite-sized pieces, including stalk (peel if tough).
Blanch or steam until just tender; amount of "crunch" a matter of personal taste.
Drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients. Chill, if desired, before serving.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Let creamed cheese and liverwurst soften.
Mix liverwurst with beaters, add some onion dip, lemon jiuce and Worcestershire to taste.
Keep sampling until it tastes ok.
Put creamed cheese in another bowl, add onion dip to it, 1 Tbsp. at a time until you get a nice spreading consistency.
Put liverwurst spread in refrigerator while getting creamed cheese ready.
Spread creamed cheese tipping over top of liverwurst ball.
sprinkle with parsley, chives, green onions, crisp bacon, or whatever.
Serve on small slices of bread.

title: yankee corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking pan with vegetable spray. Slightly beat egg and add milk, molasses and oil; blend.
Mix together the corn meal, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add wet ingredients; mix only to blend in dry ingredients.
Scrape into baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until corn bread separates from the sides of the pan and the center returns to the touch.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip. Set aside.
Mix together the pretzels, melted oleo and sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: mrs. cameron's cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake small ice cream scoops of dough on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for ten to twelve minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in greased baking dish; season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: banana applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into muffin pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine brownie mix with eggs, water, oil, and pecans in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Spread into a greased 9 inch pan.
Bake for 35-40 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Cook over boiling water until thickened (2 to 3 minutes).
Serve at once.
The secret is letting it set until it comes to room temperature.

title: luau cabbage salad
directions: Mix together dressing, sugar and curry powder.
Combine cabbage, pineapple and peanuts. Blend together and serve on a leaf of lettuce.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a sheet pan, spreading evenly.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half of this over batter and pour remaining batter over sugar mixture.	Sprinkle rest of brown sugar on top. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cracker cake
directions: Mix the cracker crumbs and pecans; set aside.
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Mix the sugar and cream of tartar to egg whites.
Add pecans and crackers to egg white mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread with Cool Whip; sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: zesty italiano
directions: Wash and remove fat from chicken breasts.
Pat chicken dry. Wash and pat dry mushrooms and zucchini.
Cut zucchini into cubes. Cut mushrooms into chunks.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken breasts and mushrooms in casserole dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce on top; cook for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put zucchini in casserole; mix in with spaghetti sauce.
Cook another 30 minutes. Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Remove from oven.
Serve chicken, spaghetti sauce, mushrooms and zucchini over seashell macaroni.
Serve with garlic bread and green salad.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: cheese cake toppings
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add cornstarch mixed with a little water; boil 10 minutes.
Let cool, then add strawberries.

title: sausage and cheddar pie
directions: Mix butter, salt, cream cheese and flour together.
Press into a pie plate.
Brown sausage and drain.
Spread over dough in pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix eggs, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook slowly over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles for about 3 minutes.
Do not brown.
Remove from heat; add salt, milk and cayenne.
Stir rapidly with wooden spoon or with wire whisk.
Cook over medium heat until sauce bubbles, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 more minute.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and shortening until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine cake flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Add milk and beat 5 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix together.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into heavily buttered 9 x 12-inch glass, ovenproof dish and bake in a 325° oven until you can touch the center and it is not soft, 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set 10 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: Bring beef to boil, add potatoes, carrots, tomatoes, leeks, parsley bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
When vegetables are tender, remove parsley and bay leaf.
Blend in yogurt or sour cream. Adjust seasonings to taste.
Simmer another minute.
The flavor of the soup is enhanced with reheating so this is a good one to make ahead.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain and add cooked noodles and soups.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Bake and melt cheese at 350°.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Cook your hamburger until it's brown.
While it's cooking, cut up the onion and put it with it.
In a separate pot, boil your noodles until they are done.
After meat is cooked, drain the grease off.
Add the whole tomatoes and juice, then add one can of whole kernel corn and one can of okra (optional).
Add the cooked noodles, and salt and pepper, just to taste.
Serve with bread and butter.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Mix milk and flour and set aside.
Bring tomatoes, water, sugar and salt to a boil in a saucepan.
Add milk and flour mixture to tomatoes; stir constantly until thickened.
Add butter, remove from heat and serve.
This is great served over meat loaf.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly the sweet potatoes, vanilla, sugar, eggs, milk and 1/2 cup of the butter.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Mix together brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 cup of remaining butter.
Sprinkle on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together flour, 1 tablespoon sugar and butter; press mixture into a pie pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Wash and stem 1 quart strawberries (leave whole); place strawberries, ends up, on pie crust. Boil water, cornstarch and 3/4 cup sugar until clear and thick; turn off and add 1 box strawberry Jell-O. Mix and cool. Pour over berries. Refrigerate 2 hours. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Grease a large Pyrex dish.
Layer buttered bread slices in bottom.
Make layers of sausage and cheese.
Repeat on top of bread.
Pour mixture of eggs, milk, salt and mustard over other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: In saucepan, heat pineapple to boiling; add jello and mix well.
Let cool slightly.
Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and chill until it can be rolled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, granulated sugar and brown sugar. Beat in egg, vanilla and peanut butter. Add flour, soda and salt. Mix until blended. Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press each ball with tines of fork to flatten. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield: about 4 dozen cookies.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet covered by foil.
Place cookie sheet in oven and turn off oven.
Bake 8 hours.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: j.l.'s low country boil
directions: Use large pot and cook outside.
Fill pot about 1/2 full with water.
Bring to boil.
Add potatoes, sausage, corn and onions. Bring to boil and cook for 10 to 15 minutes total.
Add shrimp. Cook until shrimp turn bright orange color or about 5 minutes. Remove pot and drain.
Serve on table covered with newspaper. Enjoy!
Serves 10 to 15.

title: seven cup salad
directions: For variety, use mandarin oranges or cherries.

title: shortcake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix on medium speed until well blended.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chill Jell-O to syrup.
Add cranberry sauce and nuts.
Swirl in sour cream.
Pour into mold.
Serves 6.

title: south carolina pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually; add syrup, oleo, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 360° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, butter and eggs.
Add milk and flour. Mix; add salt, baking powder and flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hidden kisses
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour and nuts until well blended.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown meat (chuck and sausage).
Drain off fat.
Add cheese and melt.
Add oregano and mix well.
Pat a tablespoon of mixture on party rye and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vidalia onion supreme
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned.
Spoon into pie shell. Add milk and 1 1/4 cups sour cream.
Blend flour with 1/4 cup sour cream and salt. Combine this with beaten eggs.
Pour over onion mixture. Bake in oven 30 minutes at 325° or until firm in center.
Garnish with crisp fried bacon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred beef with scissors.
Save enough chipped beef to put on outside.
Mix all ingredients to form a ball.
Roll in remaining dried beef.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Let cool slightly.
Heat soup with water.
Let cool.
Beat eggs and add to soup.
Add mayonnaise to soup mixture.
Melt margarine and add dressing.
Layer broccoli, some dressing, some cheese and part of soup mixture.
Then layer the rest.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Cover and bake 15 minutes longer or until brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Put in casserole dish. Layer green beans evenly over beef.
Mix milk, soup and cheese in sauce pan - heat until cheese melts.
Pour over beans and beef. Layer top with tater tots.
Bake at 350°F. until golden brown. Top with grated cheese and serve.

title: cream brulee
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored, about 5 minutes. Beat in
sugar gradually.
Beat whipping cream in a 2-quart saucepan over a medium heat just until hot.
Stir half of hot cream into egg yolks gradually.
Blend egg mixture into remaining hot cream in saucepan.
Cook; stir constantly until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
Pour into pie plate, 9-inch.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, no longer than 24 hours.
Set oven control to broil and/or 550°.
Sprinkle brown sugar over custard.
Broil with top about 5 inches from heat until sugar melts and forms a glaze, about 3 minutes.
Spoon over fruit.

title: oatmeal raisin crisp
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat shortening, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by well-rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool cookies on sheet for 2 minutes.
Makes approximately 7 1/2 dozen.

title: pate smoked salmon with shallots and dill
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, vinegar, shallots, dill and parsley.
Add drained salmon.
Beat well.
Put spread in a crock. Serve with crackers, bagels or pumpernickel bread.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: In large cooker combine beef and water.
Boil until all water is gone.
Drain grease.
Add catsup, tomato paste, onions and chili powder.
Simmer until thick, about 30 minutes.
Yields 1 gallon of chili sauce and can be frozen for several weeks.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients on stove until it boils, then boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Stir up and drop on wax paper.

title: pam's mother friend ham
directions: Place in brown grocery sack.
Put in roaster and bake at 300° to 325° for about 2 hours.
You can also press brown sugar on top of ham.
Lay pineapple rings on top; attach with cloves.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir; do not beat.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
(Test with toothpick.)
Bake in 3 loaf pans.
Will freeze well.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in large skillet.
Cover; cook over medium heat 15 minutes or longer.

title: rachel's quick cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling, then drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, egg, and enough milk to form stiff dough.
Drop small balls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together and spread on cool crust.
Combine strawberries and pineapple.
Mix strawberry jello and boiling water.
Cool and add to strawberries and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator and cool until it begins to set, then add over cream cheese layer.

title: father's pickled eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs and egg dye.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place eggs in 2 large jars.
Cover with hot liquid. Add egg dye to liquid.
Cover jar; refrigerate for 36 hours.
Will last in fridge for 2 weeks.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° in long cake pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into meat.
Brown in hot oil.
Add tomatoes, onions, garlic and wine.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add peppers and olives; cook 15 minutes, or until peppers are tender.
Serve with rice. Serves 6.

title: southwestern chicken salad
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken, cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove.

title: sweet sour kraut
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir once.

title: scotch christmas cookies
directions: Roll out between 2 sheets of waxed paper onto a wet bread board.
With cookie cutter, cut desired shapes and decorate.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in an ungreased 8-inch pan.
Add shortening, vanilla and vinegar.
Cover with one cup of water.
Stir with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Gradually stir in chocolate milk and, stirring constantly over medium heat, boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Place plastic wrap directly on surface and refrigerate 30 to 45 minutes until only slightly warm.
Quickly stir in marshmallows and morsels and pour into crust.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serves 8.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Spoon into muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: zilla's beets
directions: Cook beets whole with 2-inch tops and roots left on.
Cook until tender.
Dip in cold water and peel.
Slice or quarter beets, leaving small beets whole, using enough to fill 2-quarts, 2 pints or 6 pints.
Bring water, vinegar, sugar and spices to boil for 15 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard; cut each wing in half at joint.
On rack in broiler pan, arrange wings.
Broil 6 inches from heat 25 minutes or until browned, turning occasionally. Transfer to serving dish.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, heat Tabasco sauce, butter and vinegar.
Drizzle evenly over wings.
Serve with celery sticks and Blue cheese salad dressing for dipping.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let butter and cheese come to room temperature. Grate cheese. Cream together butter and cheese thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Form straws on ungreased cookie sheet.
Use cookie press.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: bacon wrapped scallops in dijon sauce
directions: Broil bacon until partially cooked, but not crisp.
Cut in half.
Thread pieces of papaya, green onion and scallop with bacon, intertwining onto skewers.
Arrange in broiler pan.

title: french-toasted cheese
directions: Make a sandwich with the bread and cheese, trimming cheese to neatly fit bread if necessary.
Beat egg lightly in shallow dish. Dip sandwich into egg, turning bread to coat both sides.
Fry sandwich in butter in skillet, over medium heat, until lightly browned on both sides, about 1 minute.
Gently press down sandwich as it cooks to melt cheese.
Serve immediately or wrap in aluminum foil to eat on the run within 30 minutes.

title: bananas foster
directions: Peel bananas, cut in half lengthwise, then cut pieces crosswise.
Set aside.
In a large skillet put butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Heat, stirring constantly over low flame until mixture becomes a smooth syrup.
Add bananas and baste them with syrup for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
In a small pan, carefully heat 1/2 cup rum until just warm.
Pour over bananas and carefully light with a match.
Baste bananas with sauce until flame dies.
To serve, place 1 scoop of vanilla ice cream into 6 dessert dishes.
Top with bananas and sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef salad stir-fry
directions: Combine lime juice, sugar, soy sauce, basil and mint; set aside.
In a medium nonstick skillet, coated with nonstick cooking spray, saute jalapeno, garlic and ginger for 30 seconds.
Add beef slices; stir-fry until desired doneness.
Remove from heat; add red peppers and cucumber and toss gently.
Place greens on serving platter and top with beef mixture.
Add dressing to a pan and bring to a boil, then drizzle over beef.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream bananas, eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, blending just until all ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add all items together except Pepperidge Farm dressing and put into a greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm dressing on top and add small pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: sausage-cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in a small crock-pot on low temperature. Brown sausage in a skillet.
Add sausage, Ranch dressing, Carnation milk and pimentos to melted cheese.
Let simmer on low until all is mixed well.

title: barbecue deluxe
directions: Fry ground beef and drain.
Put all other ingredients together with beef in crock-pot.
Cook slowly until done.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat and onion until well done, then add the rest. Simmer several hours.
Stir often.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Wash blackberries. Add water and bring to boiling point.
Cook until berries are soft.
Remove from heat and strain through cloth bag.
Measure liquid and bring to a boil.
Add gradually the same amount of sugar as liquid. Cook rapidly until jelly begins to thicken.
Pour into glasses.
When cool, cover with paraffin wax.

title: minestrone with tortellini
directions: Break sausage into small pieces.
Cook in large pot over medium heat.
Remove and drain.
In same pot, saute onions until tender.
Add garlic powder, beef broth, wine, tomatoes, carrots, celery, ketchup and Italian seasoning.
Bring to boil and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Skim fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes until tortellini is tender.

title: peanut orange coconut balls
directions: Crush wafers.
Mix all	together
and chill.
Make thin icing of 2 cups powdered	sugar
and orange juice and 2 tablespoons oleo.
Make walnut size balls of dough mixture;
dip in icing and roll in coconut.
Chill 24 hours.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, egg and shortening.
(Grease hands.)
Mix in flour to make soft dough. Knead it until mixed well.
Put in greased bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down.
Make into 2 loaves and put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.
Top should be golden brown and sounds hollow when tapped.
Rub with butter after done.

title: fruit dip
directions: With
electric	mixer,	blend
pudding, milk and orange juice. Slowly
add sour cream, mixing by hand.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving with your favorite fresh fruits.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Pour boiling water over top. Let stand for at least 2 hours. Squeeze or drain. Add sugar, orange juice and lemonade. Pour into 1 gallon glass container. Fill with cold water, bring to boil. Serve hot. Yields 30 servings.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Depending on size of squash, allow 1/2 per person.
Parboil whole squash in salted water until tender.
Remove; slice in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center of squash and place in bowl on equal amount of finely diced yellow cheese.
Add a little cream or milk, salt and pepper lightly, and return to squash shell.
Top with fine bread crumbs, dot with butter, and bake until cheese is melted.

title: puffy pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in each of two 8 or 10-inch pie pans.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Dip chicken into eggs, then coat with cracker crumbs.
Brown in small amount of olive oil.
Pour 1/2 jar of Prego into bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour remainder of Prego over chicken breasts.
Place 1 slice Mozzarella cheese on each chicken breast.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to your liking.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: melanie's beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in 1/2 of margarine; set aside.
In same pan, brown meat in rest of margarine.
Add to meat.
Add tomato paste, mustard and salt.
Cook, uncovered, until tender, about 45 minutes.
Combine flour and water; add to meat and stir constantly to thicken.
Reduce heat.
Add mushrooms, onion and sour cream.
Simmer gently for a short time.
Do not boil.
Serve over wide egg noodles.
Serves 6.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together thoroughly; shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs lightly in deep pan; drain.
Cream together the milk and mushroom soup.
Add soup mixture to the meatballs and simmer for about 1/2 hour.
May serve over noodles if desired.
Makes about 25 meatballs.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and eggs.
Add potatoes.
Mix in flour, one cup at a time and beat with spoon after each addition until dough is easy to handle (use only enough flour to be able to handle dough).
You will work in additional flour while kneading.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl and cover with damp cloth.
This dough will keep several days in refrigerator.
Make out and let rise about 2 hours.
Bake at 400°.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 2 cups flour, sugar and salt.
Add margarine, then tap water.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed (#6 on mixer). Add 1 cup flour.
Beat on high speed until thick and elastic for about 2 minutes.
Turn off mixer.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix honey, sugar, and oil.
Add beaten eggs, cinnamon, soda, salt, and flour.
Then add pecans, raisins, or coconut.
Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees in a jelly roll pan.
Allow to cool slightly.
Combine water, mayonnaise, and confectioners sugar and spread glaze over bars.

title: watergate
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together, then add chopped nuts and mini marshmallows.
Combine with Cool Whip.

title: noodles romanoff
directions: While noodles are hot, combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and paprika.
Put in well buttered 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until hot.
Based on 6 servings, per serving:
363 calories, 21 g. fat, 531 sodium, 79 mg cholesterol.

title: buckeyes
directions: Combine butter and peanut butter, slowly add powdered sugar. Stir to a smooth mixture; cover and refrigerate (form into balls about 2 1/2-inches).
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Using a fork, dip balls halfway into chocolate. Dry on wax paper.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine soup, water and rice in baking dish.
Place pork chops in mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter, chips and peanut butter until creamy.
Place cereal in large plastic bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over and shake and stir with spatula, coating all of the cereal.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and store in covered container.

title: bean soup
directions: Pick over beans; rinse under running water.
Combine beans and water in a large kettle.
Bring to boiling; cover.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Return to heat; add ham hock and bring to boiling, cover kettle.
Lower heat; simmer 2 hours or until beans are just tender.
Add celery, onion, carrot, potato, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour longer or until beans are very tender.
Remove bay leaf; trim fat and bone from ham hock; return meat to kettle.

title: bug killer
directions: In large bowl mix boric acid, flour and shortening.
Add water, small amount at a time, to make soft dough.
Shape in small balls and place around where bugs are.

title: best biscuits ever
directions: Mix well.
This will be somewhat of a stiff dough.
Knead just a little on floured board.
Roll thin, cut and place on greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Be sure to open the oven to get a smell of the aroma while these are baking!!

title: italian sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir well.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine
all ingredients in bowl in order listed, mixing well. Chill in refrigerator.

title: blueberry salad
directions: First Layer:
Take family size jello and add 3 1/2 cups hot water.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften the cream cheese and beat well with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add peanut butter, powdered sugar, milk, and vanilla to the cream cheese and beat well until smooth.
Gently fold the cool into the cream cheese mixture.
Put the filling into the pie shell and refrigerate.
Before serving top the pie with cool whip and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until well blended.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan, patting down firmly.
Melt the chocolate chips and spread over the mixture.
Cool just enough to firm the chocolate, then cut into bars.
